53static void CheckPreprocessingOptions(const Driver &D, const ArgList &Args) {
54 if (Arg *A =
55 Args.getLastArg(clang::driver::options::OPT_C, options::OPT_CC)) {
56 if (!Args.hasArg(options::OPT_E) && !Args.hasArg(options::OPT__SLASH_P) &&
57 !Args.hasArg(options::OPT__SLASH_EP) && !D.CCCIsCPP()) {
58 D.Diag(clang::diag::err_drv_argument_only_allowed_with)
59 << A->getBaseArg().getAsString(Args)
60 << (D.IsCLMode() ? "/E, /P or /EP" : "-E");
61 }
62 }
63}
64
65static void CheckCodeGenerationOptions(const Driver &D, const ArgList &Args) {
66 // In gcc, only ARM checks this, but it seems reasonable to check universally.
67 if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT_static))
68 if (const Arg *A =
69 Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_dynamic, options::OPT_mdynamic_no_pic))
70 D.Diag(diag::err_drv_argument_not_allowed_with) << A->getAsString(Args)
71 << "-static";
72}

74// Add backslashes to escape spaces and other backslashes.
75// This is used for the space-separated argument list specified with
76// the -dwarf-debug-flags option.
77static void EscapeSpacesAndBackslashes(const char *Arg,
78 SmallVectorImpl<char> &Res) {
79 for (; *Arg; ++Arg) {
80 switch (*Arg) {
81 default:
82 break;
83 case ' ':
84 case '\\':
85 Res.push_back('\\');
86 break;
87 }
88 Res.push_back(*Arg);
89 }
90}
91
92// Quote target names for inclusion in GNU Make dependency files.
93// Only the characters '$', '#', ' ', '\t' are quoted.
94static void QuoteTarget(StringRef Target, SmallVectorImpl<char> &Res) {
95 for (unsigned i = 0, e = Target.size(); i != e; ++i) {
96 switch (Target[i]) {
97 case ' ':
98 case '\t':
99 // Escape the preceding backslashes
100 for (int j = i - 1; j >= 0 && Target[j] == '\\'; --j)
101 Res.push_back('\\');
102
103 // Escape the space/tab
104 Res.push_back('\\');
105 break;
106 case '$':
107 Res.push_back('$');
108 break;
109 case '#':
110 Res.push_back('\\');
111 break;
112 default:
113 break;
114 }
115
116 Res.push_back(Target[i]);
117 }
118}

120/// Apply \a Work on the current tool chain \a RegularToolChain and any other
121/// offloading tool chain that is associated with the current action \a JA.
122static void
123forAllAssociatedToolChains(Compilation &C, const JobAction &JA,
124 const ToolChain &RegularToolChain,
125 llvm::function_ref<void(const ToolChain &)> Work) {
126 // Apply Work on the current/regular tool chain.
127 Work(RegularToolChain);
128
129 // Apply Work on all the offloading tool chains associated with the current
130 // action.
131 if (JA.isHostOffloading(Action::OFK_Cuda))
132 Work(*C.getSingleOffloadToolChain<Action::OFK_Cuda>());
133 else if (JA.isDeviceOffloading(Action::OFK_Cuda))
134 Work(*C.getSingleOffloadToolChain<Action::OFK_Host>());
135 else if (JA.isHostOffloading(Action::OFK_HIP))
136 Work(*C.getSingleOffloadToolChain<Action::OFK_HIP>());
137 else if (JA.isDeviceOffloading(Action::OFK_HIP))
138 Work(*C.getSingleOffloadToolChain<Action::OFK_Host>());
139
140 if (JA.isHostOffloading(Action::OFK_OpenMP)) {
141 auto TCs = C.getOffloadToolChains<Action::OFK_OpenMP>();
142 for (auto II = TCs.first, IE = TCs.second; II != IE; ++II)
143 Work(*II->second);
144 } else if (JA.isDeviceOffloading(Action::OFK_OpenMP))
145 Work(*C.getSingleOffloadToolChain<Action::OFK_Host>());
146
147 //
148 // TODO: Add support for other offloading programming models here.
149 //
150}

152/// This is a helper function for validating the optional refinement step
153/// parameter in reciprocal argument strings. Return false if there is an error
154/// parsing the refinement step. Otherwise, return true and set the Position
155/// of the refinement step in the input string.
156static bool getRefinementStep(StringRef In, const Driver &D,
157 const Arg &A, size_t &Position) {
158 const char RefinementStepToken = ':';
159 Position = In.find(RefinementStepToken);
160 if (Position != StringRef::npos) {
161 StringRef Option = A.getOption().getName();
162 StringRef RefStep = In.substr(Position + 1);
163 // Allow exactly one numeric character for the additional refinement
164 // step parameter. This is reasonable for all currently-supported
165 // operations and architectures because we would expect that a larger value
166 // of refinement steps would cause the estimate "optimization" to
167 // under-perform the native operation. Also, if the estimate does not
168 // converge quickly, it probably will not ever converge, so further
169 // refinement steps will not produce a better answer.
170 if (RefStep.size() != 1) {
171 D.Diag(diag::err_drv_invalid_value) << Option << RefStep;
172 return false;
173 }
174 char RefStepChar = RefStep[0];
175 if (RefStepChar < '0' || RefStepChar > '9') {
176 D.Diag(diag::err_drv_invalid_value) << Option << RefStep;
177 return false;
178 }
179 }
180 return true;
181}

183/// The -mrecip flag requires processing of many optional parameters.
184static void ParseMRecip(const Driver &D, const ArgList &Args,
185 ArgStringList &OutStrings) {
186 StringRef DisabledPrefixIn = "!";
187 StringRef DisabledPrefixOut = "!";
188 StringRef EnabledPrefixOut = "";
189 StringRef Out = "-mrecip=";
190
191 Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_mrecip, options::OPT_mrecip_EQ);
192 if (!A)
193 return;
194
195 unsigned NumOptions = A->getNumValues();
196 if (NumOptions == 0) {
197 // No option is the same as "all".
198 OutStrings.push_back(Args.MakeArgString(Out + "all"));
199 return;
200 }
201
202 // Pass through "all", "none", or "default" with an optional refinement step.
203 if (NumOptions == 1) {
204 StringRef Val = A->getValue(0);
205 size_t RefStepLoc;
206 if (!getRefinementStep(Val, D, *A, RefStepLoc))
207 return;
208 StringRef ValBase = Val.slice(0, RefStepLoc);
209 if (ValBase == "all" || ValBase == "none" || ValBase == "default") {
210 OutStrings.push_back(Args.MakeArgString(Out + Val));
211 return;
212 }
213 }
214
215 // Each reciprocal type may be enabled or disabled individually.
216 // Check each input value for validity, concatenate them all back together,
217 // and pass through.
218
219 llvm::StringMap<bool> OptionStrings;
220 OptionStrings.insert(std::make_pair("divd", false));
221 OptionStrings.insert(std::make_pair("divf", false));
222 OptionStrings.insert(std::make_pair("vec-divd", false));
223 OptionStrings.insert(std::make_pair("vec-divf", false));
224 OptionStrings.insert(std::make_pair("sqrtd", false));
225 OptionStrings.insert(std::make_pair("sqrtf", false));
226 OptionStrings.insert(std::make_pair("vec-sqrtd", false));
227 OptionStrings.insert(std::make_pair("vec-sqrtf", false));
228
229 for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumOptions; ++i) {
230 StringRef Val = A->getValue(i);
231
232 bool IsDisabled = Val.startswith(DisabledPrefixIn);
233 // Ignore the disablement token for string matching.
234 if (IsDisabled)
235 Val = Val.substr(1);
236
237 size_t RefStep;
238 if (!getRefinementStep(Val, D, *A, RefStep))
239 return;
240
241 StringRef ValBase = Val.slice(0, RefStep);
242 llvm::StringMap<bool>::iterator OptionIter = OptionStrings.find(ValBase);
243 if (OptionIter == OptionStrings.end()) {
244 // Try again specifying float suffix.
245 OptionIter = OptionStrings.find(ValBase.str() + 'f');
246 if (OptionIter == OptionStrings.end()) {
247 // The input name did not match any known option string.
248 D.Diag(diag::err_drv_unknown_argument) << Val;
249 return;
250 }
251 // The option was specified without a float or double suffix.
252 // Make sure that the double entry was not already specified.
253 // The float entry will be checked below.
254 if (OptionStrings[ValBase.str() + 'd']) {
255 D.Diag(diag::err_drv_invalid_value) << A->getOption().getName() << Val;
256 return;
257 }
258 }
259
260 if (OptionIter->second == true) {
261 // Duplicate option specified.
262 D.Diag(diag::err_drv_invalid_value) << A->getOption().getName() << Val;
263 return;
264 }
265
266 // Mark the matched option as found. Do not allow duplicate specifiers.
267 OptionIter->second = true;
268
269 // If the precision was not specified, also mark the double entry as found.
270 if (ValBase.back() != 'f' && ValBase.back() != 'd')
271 OptionStrings[ValBase.str() + 'd'] = true;
272
273 // Build the output string.
274 StringRef Prefix = IsDisabled ? DisabledPrefixOut : EnabledPrefixOut;
275 Out = Args.MakeArgString(Out + Prefix + Val);
276 if (i != NumOptions - 1)
277 Out = Args.MakeArgString(Out + ",");
278 }
279
280 OutStrings.push_back(Args.MakeArgString(Out));
281}

283/// The -mprefer-vector-width option accepts either a positive integer
284/// or the string "none".
285static void ParseMPreferVectorWidth(const Driver &D, const ArgList &Args,
286 ArgStringList &CmdArgs) {
287 Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_mprefer_vector_width_EQ);
288 if (!A)
289 return;
290
291 StringRef Value = A->getValue();
292 if (Value == "none") {
293 CmdArgs.push_back("-mprefer-vector-width=none");
294 } else {
295 unsigned Width;
296 if (Value.getAsInteger(10, Width)) {
297 D.Diag(diag::err_drv_invalid_value) << A->getOption().getName() << Value;
298 return;
299 }
300 CmdArgs.push_back(Args.MakeArgString("-mprefer-vector-width=" + Value));
301 }
302}

309static void getTargetFeatures(const ToolChain &TC, const llvm::Triple &Triple,
310 const ArgList &Args, ArgStringList &CmdArgs,
311 bool ForAS) {
312 const Driver &D = TC.getDriver();
313 std::vector<StringRef> Features;
314 switch (Triple.getArch()) {
315 default:
316 break;
317 case llvm::Triple::mips:
318 case llvm::Triple::mipsel:
319 case llvm::Triple::mips64:
320 case llvm::Triple::mips64el:
321 case llvm::Triple::cheri:
322 mips::getMIPSTargetFeatures(D, Triple, Args, Features);
323 break;
324
325 case llvm::Triple::arm:
326 case llvm::Triple::armeb:
327 case llvm::Triple::thumb:
328 case llvm::Triple::thumbeb:
329 arm::getARMTargetFeatures(TC, Triple, Args, CmdArgs, Features, ForAS);
330 break;
331
332 case llvm::Triple::ppc:
333 case llvm::Triple::ppc64:
334 case llvm::Triple::ppc64le:
335 ppc::getPPCTargetFeatures(D, Triple, Args, Features);
336 break;
337 case llvm::Triple::riscv32:
338 case llvm::Triple::riscv64:
339 riscv::getRISCVTargetFeatures(D, Args, Features);
340 break;
341 case llvm::Triple::systemz:
342 systemz::getSystemZTargetFeatures(Args, Features);
343 break;
344 case llvm::Triple::aarch64:
345 case llvm::Triple::aarch64_be:
346 aarch64::getAArch64TargetFeatures(D, Triple, Args, Features);
347 break;
348 case llvm::Triple::x86:
349 case llvm::Triple::x86_64:
350 x86::getX86TargetFeatures(D, Triple, Args, Features);
351 break;
352 case llvm::Triple::hexagon:
353 hexagon::getHexagonTargetFeatures(D, Args, Features);
354 break;
355 case llvm::Triple::wasm32:
356 case llvm::Triple::wasm64:
357 getWebAssemblyTargetFeatures(Args, Features);
358 break;
359 case llvm::Triple::sparc:
360 case llvm::Triple::sparcel:
361 case llvm::Triple::sparcv9:
362 sparc::getSparcTargetFeatures(D, Args, Features);
363 break;
364 case llvm::Triple::r600:
365 case llvm::Triple::amdgcn:
366 amdgpu::getAMDGPUTargetFeatures(D, Args, Features);
367 break;
368 case llvm::Triple::msp430:
369 msp430::getMSP430TargetFeatures(D, Args, Features);
370 }
371
372 // Find the last of each feature.
373 llvm::StringMap<unsigned> LastOpt;
374 for (unsigned I = 0, N = Features.size(); I < N; ++I) {
375 StringRef Name = Features[I];
376 assert(Name[0] == '-' || Name[0] == '+');
377 LastOpt[Name.drop_front(1)] = I;
378 }
379
380 for (unsigned I = 0, N = Features.size(); I < N; ++I) {
381 // If this feature was overridden, ignore it.
382 StringRef Name = Features[I];
383 llvm::StringMap<unsigned>::iterator LastI = LastOpt.find(Name.drop_front(1));
384 assert(LastI != LastOpt.end());
385 unsigned Last = LastI->second;
386 if (Last != I)
387 continue;
388
389 CmdArgs.push_back("-target-feature");
390 CmdArgs.push_back(Name.data());
391 }
392}

394static bool
395shouldUseExceptionTablesForObjCExceptions(const ObjCRuntime &runtime,
396 const llvm::Triple &Triple) {
397 // We use the zero-cost exception tables for Objective-C if the non-fragile
398 // ABI is enabled or when compiling for x86_64 and ARM on Snow Leopard and
399 // later.
400 if (runtime.isNonFragile())
401 return true;
402
403 if (!Triple.isMacOSX())
404 return false;
405
406 return (!Triple.isMacOSXVersionLT(10, 5) &&
407 (Triple.getArch() == llvm::Triple::x86_64 ||
408 Triple.getArch() == llvm::Triple::arm));
409}

411/// Adds exception related arguments to the driver command arguments. There's a
412/// master flag, -fexceptions and also language specific flags to enable/disable
413/// C++ and Objective-C exceptions. This makes it possible to for example
414/// disable C++ exceptions but enable Objective-C exceptions.
415static void addExceptionArgs(const ArgList &Args, types::ID InputType,
416 const ToolChain &TC, bool KernelOrKext,
417 const ObjCRuntime &objcRuntime,
418 ArgStringList &CmdArgs) {
419 const llvm::Triple &Triple = TC.getTriple();
420
421 if (KernelOrKext) {
422 // -mkernel and -fapple-kext imply no exceptions, so claim exception related
423 // arguments now to avoid warnings about unused arguments.
424 Args.ClaimAllArgs(options::OPT_fexceptions);
425 Args.ClaimAllArgs(options::OPT_fno_exceptions);
426 Args.ClaimAllArgs(options::OPT_fobjc_exceptions);
427 Args.ClaimAllArgs(options::OPT_fno_objc_exceptions);
428 Args.ClaimAllArgs(options::OPT_fcxx_exceptions);
429 Args.ClaimAllArgs(options::OPT_fno_cxx_exceptions);
430 return;
431 }
432
433 // See if the user explicitly enabled exceptions.
434 bool EH = Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_fexceptions, options::OPT_fno_exceptions,
435 false);
436
437 // Obj-C exceptions are enabled by default, regardless of -fexceptions. This
438 // is not necessarily sensible, but follows GCC.
439 if (types::isObjC(InputType) &&
440 Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_fobjc_exceptions,
441 options::OPT_fno_objc_exceptions, true)) {
442 CmdArgs.push_back("-fobjc-exceptions");
443
444 EH |= shouldUseExceptionTablesForObjCExceptions(objcRuntime, Triple);
445 }
446
447 if (types::isCXX(InputType)) {
448 // Disable C++ EH by default on XCore and PS4.
449 bool CXXExceptionsEnabled =
450 Triple.getArch() != llvm::Triple::xcore && !Triple.isPS4CPU();
451 Arg *ExceptionArg = Args.getLastArg(
452 options::OPT_fcxx_exceptions, options::OPT_fno_cxx_exceptions,
453 options::OPT_fexceptions, options::OPT_fno_exceptions);
454
455 if (ExceptionArg)
456 CXXExceptionsEnabled =
457 ExceptionArg->getOption().matches(options::OPT_fcxx_exceptions) ||
458 ExceptionArg->getOption().matches(options::OPT_fexceptions);
459
460 if (CXXExceptionsEnabled) {
461 CmdArgs.push_back("-fcxx-exceptions");
462
463 EH = true;
464 }
465 }
466
467 if (EH)
468 CmdArgs.push_back("-fexceptions");
469}

471static bool ShouldDisableAutolink(const ArgList &Args, const ToolChain &TC) {
472 bool Default = true;
473 if (TC.getTriple().isOSDarwin()) {
474 // The native darwin assembler doesn't support the linker_option directives,
475 // so we disable them if we think the .s file will be passed to it.
476 Default = TC.useIntegratedAs();
477 }
478 return !Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_fautolink, options::OPT_fno_autolink,
479 Default);
480}

482static bool ShouldDisableDwarfDirectory(const ArgList &Args,
483 const ToolChain &TC) {
484 bool UseDwarfDirectory =
485 Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_fdwarf_directory_asm,
486 options::OPT_fno_dwarf_directory_asm, TC.useIntegratedAs());
487 return !UseDwarfDirectory;
488}

490// Convert an arg of the form "-gN" or "-ggdbN" or one of their aliases
491// to the corresponding DebugInfoKind.
492static codegenoptions::DebugInfoKind DebugLevelToInfoKind(const Arg &A) {
493 assert(A.getOption().matches(options::OPT_gN_Group) &&
494 "Not a -g option that specifies a debug-info level");
495 if (A.getOption().matches(options::OPT_g0) ||
496 A.getOption().matches(options::OPT_ggdb0))
497 return codegenoptions::NoDebugInfo;
498 if (A.getOption().matches(options::OPT_gline_tables_only) ||
499 A.getOption().matches(options::OPT_ggdb1))
500 return codegenoptions::DebugLineTablesOnly;
501 if (A.getOption().matches(options::OPT_gline_directives_only))
502 return codegenoptions::DebugDirectivesOnly;
503 return codegenoptions::LimitedDebugInfo;
504}

506static bool mustUseNonLeafFramePointerForTarget(const llvm::Triple &Triple) {
507 switch (Triple.getArch()){
508 default:
509 return false;
510 case llvm::Triple::arm:
511 case llvm::Triple::thumb:
512 // ARM Darwin targets require a frame pointer to be always present to aid
513 // offline debugging via backtraces.
514 return Triple.isOSDarwin();
515 }
516}
517
518static bool useFramePointerForTargetByDefault(const ArgList &Args,
519 const llvm::Triple &Triple) {
520 switch (Triple.getArch()) {
521 case llvm::Triple::xcore:
522 case llvm::Triple::wasm32:
523 case llvm::Triple::wasm64:
524 case llvm::Triple::msp430:
525 // XCore never wants frame pointers, regardless of OS.
526 // WebAssembly never wants frame pointers.
527 return false;
528 case llvm::Triple::riscv32:
529 case llvm::Triple::riscv64:
530 return !areOptimizationsEnabled(Args);
531 default:
532 break;
533 }
534
535 if (Triple.isOSNetBSD()) {
536 return !areOptimizationsEnabled(Args);
537 }
538
539 if (Triple.isOSOpenBSD()) {
540 switch (Triple.getArch()) {
541 case llvm::Triple::mips64:
542 case llvm::Triple::mips64el:
543 case llvm::Triple::ppc:
544 case llvm::Triple::x86:
545 case llvm::Triple::x86_64:
546 return !areOptimizationsEnabled(Args);
547 default:
548 return true;
549 }
550 }
551
552 if (Triple.isOSLinux() || Triple.getOS() == llvm::Triple::CloudABI ||
553 Triple.isOSHurd()) {
554 switch (Triple.getArch()) {
555 // Don't use a frame pointer on linux if optimizing for certain targets.
556 case llvm::Triple::mips64:
557 case llvm::Triple::mips64el:
558 case llvm::Triple::mips:
559 case llvm::Triple::mipsel:
560 case llvm::Triple::ppc:
561 case llvm::Triple::ppc64:
562 case llvm::Triple::ppc64le:
563 case llvm::Triple::systemz:
564 case llvm::Triple::x86:
565 case llvm::Triple::x86_64:
566 return !areOptimizationsEnabled(Args);
567 default:
568 return true;
569 }
570 }
571
572 if (Triple.isOSWindows()) {
573 switch (Triple.getArch()) {
574 case llvm::Triple::x86:
575 return !areOptimizationsEnabled(Args);
576 case llvm::Triple::x86_64:
577 return Triple.isOSBinFormatMachO();
578 case llvm::Triple::arm:
579 case llvm::Triple::thumb:
580 // Windows on ARM builds with FPO disabled to aid fast stack walking
581 return true;
582 default:
583 // All other supported Windows ISAs use xdata unwind information, so frame
584 // pointers are not generally useful.
585 return false;
586 }
587 }
588
589 return true;
590}
591
592static bool shouldUseFramePointer(const ArgList &Args,
593 const llvm::Triple &Triple) {
594 if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_fno_omit_frame_pointer,
595 options::OPT_fomit_frame_pointer))
596 return A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_fno_omit_frame_pointer) ||
597 mustUseNonLeafFramePointerForTarget(Triple);
598
599 if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT_pg))
600 return true;
601
602 return useFramePointerForTargetByDefault(Args, Triple);
603}
604
605static bool shouldUseLeafFramePointer(const ArgList &Args,
606 const llvm::Triple &Triple) {
607 if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_mno_omit_leaf_frame_pointer,
608 options::OPT_momit_leaf_frame_pointer))
609 return A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_mno_omit_leaf_frame_pointer);
610
611 if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT_pg))
612 return true;
613
614 if (Triple.isPS4CPU())
615 return false;
616
617 return useFramePointerForTargetByDefault(Args, Triple);
618}

621static void addDebugCompDirArg(const ArgList &Args, ArgStringList &CmdArgs,
622 const llvm::vfs::FileSystem &VFS) {
623 if (llvm::ErrorOr<std::string> CWD = VFS.getCurrentWorkingDirectory()) {

629/// Add a CC1 and CC1AS option to specify the debug file path prefix map.
630static void addDebugPrefixMapArg(const Driver &D, const ArgList &Args, ArgStringList &CmdArgs) {
631 for (const Arg *A : Args.filtered(options::OPT_fdebug_prefix_map_EQ)) {
632 StringRef Map = A->getValue();
633 if (Map.find('=') == StringRef::npos)
634 D.Diag(diag::err_drv_invalid_argument_to_fdebug_prefix_map) << Map;
635 else
636 CmdArgs.push_back(Args.MakeArgString("-fdebug-prefix-map=" + Map));
637 A->claim();
638 }
639}

641/// Vectorize at all optimization levels greater than 1 except for -Oz.
642/// For -Oz the loop vectorizer is disable, while the slp vectorizer is enabled.
643static bool shouldEnableVectorizerAtOLevel(const ArgList &Args, bool isSlpVec) {
644 if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_O_Group)) {
645 if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_O4) ||
646 A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_Ofast))
647 return true;
648
649 if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_O0))
650 return false;
651
652 assert(A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_O) && "Must have a -O flag");
653
654 // Vectorize -Os.
655 StringRef S(A->getValue());
656 if (S == "s")
657 return true;
658
659 // Don't vectorize -Oz, unless it's the slp vectorizer.
660 if (S == "z")
661 return isSlpVec;
662
663 unsigned OptLevel = 0;
664 if (S.getAsInteger(10, OptLevel))
665 return false;
666
667 return OptLevel > 1;
668 }
669
670 return false;
671}

673/// Add -x lang to \p CmdArgs for \p Input.
674static void addDashXForInput(const ArgList &Args, const InputInfo &Input,
675 ArgStringList &CmdArgs) {
676 // When using -verify-pch, we don't want to provide the type
677 // 'precompiled-header' if it was inferred from the file extension
678 if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT_verify_pch) && Input.getType() == types::TY_PCH)
679 return;
680
681 CmdArgs.push_back("-x");
682 if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT_rewrite_objc))
683 CmdArgs.push_back(types::getTypeName(types::TY_PP_ObjCXX));
684 else {
685 // Map the driver type to the frontend type. This is mostly an identity
686 // mapping, except that the distinction between module interface units
687 // and other source files does not exist at the frontend layer.
688 const char *ClangType;
689 switch (Input.getType()) {
690 case types::TY_CXXModule:
691 ClangType = "c++";
692 break;
693 case types::TY_PP_CXXModule:
694 ClangType = "c++-cpp-output";
695 break;
696 default:
697 ClangType = types::getTypeName(Input.getType());
698 break;
699 }
700 CmdArgs.push_back(ClangType);
701 }
702}

704static void appendUserToPath(SmallVectorImpl<char> &Result) {
705#ifdef LLVM_ON_UNIX
706 const char *Username = getenv("LOGNAME");
707#else
708 const char *Username = getenv("USERNAME");
709#endif
710 if (Username) {
711 // Validate that LoginName can be used in a path, and get its length.
712 size_t Len = 0;
713 for (const char *P = Username; *P; ++P, ++Len) {
714 if (!clang::isAlphanumeric(*P) && *P != '_') {
715 Username = nullptr;
716 break;
717 }
718 }
719
720 if (Username && Len > 0) {
721 Result.append(Username, Username + Len);
722 return;
723 }
724 }
725
726// Fallback to user id.
727#ifdef LLVM_ON_UNIX
728 std::string UID = llvm::utostr(getuid());
729#else
730 // FIXME: Windows seems to have an 'SID' that might work.
731 std::string UID = "9999";
732#endif
733 Result.append(UID.begin(), UID.end());
734}

736static void addPGOAndCoverageFlags(const ToolChain &TC, Compilation &C,
737 const Driver &D, const InputInfo &Output,
738 const ArgList &Args,
739 ArgStringList &CmdArgs) {
740
741 auto *PGOGenerateArg = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_fprofile_generate,
742 options::OPT_fprofile_generate_EQ,
743 options::OPT_fno_profile_generate);
744 if (PGOGenerateArg &&
745 PGOGenerateArg->getOption().matches(options::OPT_fno_profile_generate))
746 PGOGenerateArg = nullptr;
747
748 auto *CSPGOGenerateArg = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_fcs_profile_generate,
749 options::OPT_fcs_profile_generate_EQ,
750 options::OPT_fno_profile_generate);
751 if (CSPGOGenerateArg &&
752 CSPGOGenerateArg->getOption().matches(options::OPT_fno_profile_generate))
753 CSPGOGenerateArg = nullptr;
754
755 auto *ProfileGenerateArg = Args.getLastArg(
756 options::OPT_fprofile_instr_generate,
757 options::OPT_fprofile_instr_generate_EQ,
758 options::OPT_fno_profile_instr_generate);
759 if (ProfileGenerateArg &&
760 ProfileGenerateArg->getOption().matches(
761 options::OPT_fno_profile_instr_generate))
762 ProfileGenerateArg = nullptr;
763
764 if (PGOGenerateArg && ProfileGenerateArg)
765 D.Diag(diag::err_drv_argument_not_allowed_with)
766 << PGOGenerateArg->getSpelling() << ProfileGenerateArg->getSpelling();
767
768 auto *ProfileUseArg = getLastProfileUseArg(Args);
769
770 if (PGOGenerateArg && ProfileUseArg)
771 D.Diag(diag::err_drv_argument_not_allowed_with)
772 << ProfileUseArg->getSpelling() << PGOGenerateArg->getSpelling();
773
774 if (ProfileGenerateArg && ProfileUseArg)
775 D.Diag(diag::err_drv_argument_not_allowed_with)
776 << ProfileGenerateArg->getSpelling() << ProfileUseArg->getSpelling();
777
778 if (CSPGOGenerateArg && PGOGenerateArg)
779 D.Diag(diag::err_drv_argument_not_allowed_with)
780 << CSPGOGenerateArg->getSpelling() << PGOGenerateArg->getSpelling();
781
782 if (ProfileGenerateArg) {
783 if (ProfileGenerateArg->getOption().matches(
784 options::OPT_fprofile_instr_generate_EQ))
785 CmdArgs.push_back(Args.MakeArgString(Twine("-fprofile-instrument-path=") +
786 ProfileGenerateArg->getValue()));
787 // The default is to use Clang Instrumentation.
788 CmdArgs.push_back("-fprofile-instrument=clang");
789 if (TC.getTriple().isWindowsMSVCEnvironment()) {
790 // Add dependent lib for clang_rt.profile
791 CmdArgs.push_back(Args.MakeArgString("--dependent-lib=" +
792 TC.getCompilerRT(Args, "profile")));
793 }
794 }
795
796 Arg *PGOGenArg = nullptr;
797 if (PGOGenerateArg) {
798 assert(!CSPGOGenerateArg);
799 PGOGenArg = PGOGenerateArg;
800 CmdArgs.push_back("-fprofile-instrument=llvm");
801 }
802 if (CSPGOGenerateArg) {
803 assert(!PGOGenerateArg);
804 PGOGenArg = CSPGOGenerateArg;
805 CmdArgs.push_back("-fprofile-instrument=csllvm");
806 }
807 if (PGOGenArg) {
808 if (TC.getTriple().isWindowsMSVCEnvironment()) {
809 CmdArgs.push_back(Args.MakeArgString("--dependent-lib=" +
810 TC.getCompilerRT(Args, "profile")));
811 }
812 if (PGOGenArg->getOption().matches(
813 PGOGenerateArg ? options::OPT_fprofile_generate_EQ
814 : options::OPT_fcs_profile_generate_EQ)) {
815 SmallString<128> Path(PGOGenArg->getValue());
816 llvm::sys::path::append(Path, "default_%m.profraw");
817 CmdArgs.push_back(
818 Args.MakeArgString(Twine("-fprofile-instrument-path=") + Path));
819 }
820 }
821
822 if (ProfileUseArg) {
823 if (ProfileUseArg->getOption().matches(options::OPT_fprofile_instr_use_EQ))
824 CmdArgs.push_back(Args.MakeArgString(
825 Twine("-fprofile-instrument-use-path=") + ProfileUseArg->getValue()));
826 else if ((ProfileUseArg->getOption().matches(
827 options::OPT_fprofile_use_EQ) ||
828 ProfileUseArg->getOption().matches(
829 options::OPT_fprofile_instr_use))) {
830 SmallString<128> Path(
831 ProfileUseArg->getNumValues() == 0 ? "" : ProfileUseArg->getValue());
832 if (Path.empty() || llvm::sys::fs::is_directory(Path))
833 llvm::sys::path::append(Path, "default.profdata");
834 CmdArgs.push_back(
835 Args.MakeArgString(Twine("-fprofile-instrument-use-path=") + Path));
836 }
837 }
838
839 if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT_ftest_coverage) ||
840 Args.hasArg(options::OPT_coverage))
841 CmdArgs.push_back("-femit-coverage-notes");
842 if (Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_fprofile_arcs, options::OPT_fno_profile_arcs,
843 false) ||
844 Args.hasArg(options::OPT_coverage))
845 CmdArgs.push_back("-femit-coverage-data");
846
847 if (Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_fcoverage_mapping,
848 options::OPT_fno_coverage_mapping, false)) {
849 if (!ProfileGenerateArg)
850 D.Diag(clang::diag::err_drv_argument_only_allowed_with)
851 << "-fcoverage-mapping"
852 << "-fprofile-instr-generate";
853
854 CmdArgs.push_back("-fcoverage-mapping");
855 }
856
857 if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT_fprofile_exclude_files_EQ)) {
858 auto *Arg = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_fprofile_exclude_files_EQ);
859 if (!Args.hasArg(options::OPT_coverage))
860 D.Diag(clang::diag::err_drv_argument_only_allowed_with)
861 << "-fprofile-exclude-files="
862 << "--coverage";
863
864 StringRef v = Arg->getValue();
865 CmdArgs.push_back(
866 Args.MakeArgString(Twine("-fprofile-exclude-files=" + v)));
867 }
868
869 if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT_fprofile_filter_files_EQ)) {
870 auto *Arg = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_fprofile_filter_files_EQ);
871 if (!Args.hasArg(options::OPT_coverage))
872 D.Diag(clang::diag::err_drv_argument_only_allowed_with)
873 << "-fprofile-filter-files="
874 << "--coverage";
875
876 StringRef v = Arg->getValue();
877 CmdArgs.push_back(Args.MakeArgString(Twine("-fprofile-filter-files=" + v)));
878 }
879
880 if (C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_c) ||
881 C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT_S)) {
882 if (Output.isFilename()) {
883 CmdArgs.push_back("-coverage-notes-file");
884 SmallString<128> OutputFilename;
885 if (Arg *FinalOutput = C.getArgs().getLastArg(options::OPT_o))
886 OutputFilename = FinalOutput->getValue();
887 else
888 OutputFilename = llvm::sys::path::filename(Output.getBaseInput());
889 SmallString<128> CoverageFilename = OutputFilename;
890 if (llvm::sys::path::is_relative(CoverageFilename))
891 (void)D.getVFS().makeAbsolute(CoverageFilename);
892 llvm::sys::path::replace_extension(CoverageFilename, "gcno");
893 CmdArgs.push_back(Args.MakeArgString(CoverageFilename));
894
895 // Leave -fprofile-dir= an unused argument unless .gcda emission is
896 // enabled. To be polite, with '-fprofile-arcs -fno-profile-arcs' consider
897 // the flag used. There is no -fno-profile-dir, so the user has no
898 // targeted way to suppress the warning.
899 if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT_fprofile_arcs) ||
900 Args.hasArg(options::OPT_coverage)) {
901 CmdArgs.push_back("-coverage-data-file");
902 if (Arg *FProfileDir = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_fprofile_dir)) {
903 CoverageFilename = FProfileDir->getValue();
904 llvm::sys::path::append(CoverageFilename, OutputFilename);
905 }
906 llvm::sys::path::replace_extension(CoverageFilename, "gcda");
907 CmdArgs.push_back(Args.MakeArgString(CoverageFilename));
908 }
909 }
910 }
911}

913/// Check whether the given input tree contains any compilation actions.
914static bool ContainsCompileAction(const Action *A) {
915 if (isa<CompileJobAction>(A) || isa<BackendJobAction>(A))
916 return true;
917
918 for (const auto &AI : A->inputs())
919 if (ContainsCompileAction(AI))
920 return true;
921
922 return false;
923}

925/// Check if -relax-all should be passed to the internal assembler.
926/// This is done by default when compiling non-assembler source with -O0.
927static bool UseRelaxAll(Compilation &C, const ArgList &Args) {
928 bool RelaxDefault = true;
929
930 if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_O_Group))
931 RelaxDefault = A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_O0);
932
933 if (RelaxDefault) {
934 RelaxDefault = false;
935 for (const auto &Act : C.getActions()) {
936 if (ContainsCompileAction(Act)) {
937 RelaxDefault = true;
938 break;
939 }
940 }
941 }
942
943 return Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_mrelax_all, options::OPT_mno_relax_all,
944 RelaxDefault);
945}

947// Extract the integer N from a string spelled "-dwarf-N", returning 0
948// on mismatch. The StringRef input (rather than an Arg) allows
949// for use by the "-Xassembler" option parser.
950static unsigned DwarfVersionNum(StringRef ArgValue) {
951 return llvm::StringSwitch<unsigned>(ArgValue)
952 .Case("-gdwarf-2", 2)
953 .Case("-gdwarf-3", 3)
954 .Case("-gdwarf-4", 4)
955 .Case("-gdwarf-5", 5)
956 .Default(0);
957}

959static void RenderDebugEnablingArgs(const ArgList &Args, ArgStringList &CmdArgs,
960 codegenoptions::DebugInfoKind DebugInfoKind,
961 unsigned DwarfVersion,
962 llvm::DebuggerKind DebuggerTuning) {
963 switch (DebugInfoKind) {
964 case codegenoptions::DebugDirectivesOnly:
965 CmdArgs.push_back("-debug-info-kind=line-directives-only");
966 break;
967 case codegenoptions::DebugLineTablesOnly:
968 CmdArgs.push_back("-debug-info-kind=line-tables-only");
969 break;
970 case codegenoptions::LimitedDebugInfo:
971 CmdArgs.push_back("-debug-info-kind=limited");
972 break;
973 case codegenoptions::FullDebugInfo:
974 CmdArgs.push_back("-debug-info-kind=standalone");
975 break;
976 default:
977 break;
978 }
979 if (DwarfVersion > 0)
980 CmdArgs.push_back(
981 Args.MakeArgString("-dwarf-version=" + Twine(DwarfVersion)));
982 switch (DebuggerTuning) {
983 case llvm::DebuggerKind::GDB:
984 CmdArgs.push_back("-debugger-tuning=gdb");
985 break;
986 case llvm::DebuggerKind::LLDB:
987 CmdArgs.push_back("-debugger-tuning=lldb");
988 break;
989 case llvm::DebuggerKind::SCE:
990 CmdArgs.push_back("-debugger-tuning=sce");
991 break;
992 default:
993 break;
994 }

997static bool checkDebugInfoOption(const Arg *A, const ArgList &Args,
998 const Driver &D, const ToolChain &TC) {
999 assert(A && "Expected non-nullptr argument.");
1000 if (TC.supportsDebugInfoOption(A))
1001 return true;

1003 << A->getAsString(Args) << TC.getTripleString();

1007static void RenderDebugInfoCompressionArgs(const ArgList &Args,
1008 ArgStringList &CmdArgs,
1009 const Driver &D,
1010 const ToolChain &TC) {
1011 const Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_gz, options::OPT_gz_EQ);
1012 if (!A)
1013 return;
1014 if (checkDebugInfoOption(A, Args, D, TC)) {
1015 if (A->getOption().getID() == options::OPT_gz) {
1016 if (llvm::zlib::isAvailable())
1017 CmdArgs.push_back("--compress-debug-sections");
1018 else
1019 D.Diag(diag::warn_debug_compression_unavailable);
1020 return;
1021 }
1022
1023 StringRef Value = A->getValue();
1024 if (Value == "none") {
1025 CmdArgs.push_back("--compress-debug-sections=none");
1026 } else if (Value == "zlib" || Value == "zlib-gnu") {
1027 if (llvm::zlib::isAvailable()) {
1028 CmdArgs.push_back(
1029 Args.MakeArgString("--compress-debug-sections=" + Twine(Value)));
1030 } else {
1031 D.Diag(diag::warn_debug_compression_unavailable);
1032 }
1033 } else {
1034 D.Diag(diag::err_drv_unsupported_option_argument)
1035 << A->getOption().getName() << Value;
1036 }
1037 }

1057
1058void Clang::AddPreprocessingOptions(Compilation &C, const JobAction &JA,
1059 const Driver &D, const ArgList &Args,
1060 ArgStringList &CmdArgs,
1061 const InputInfo &Output,
1062 const InputInfoList &Inputs) const {
1063 Arg *A;
1064 const bool IsIAMCU = getToolChain().getTriple().isOSIAMCU();
1065
1066 CheckPreprocessingOptions(D, Args);
1067
1068 Args.AddLastArg(CmdArgs, options::OPT_C);
1069 Args.AddLastArg(CmdArgs, options::OPT_CC);
1070
1071 // Handle dependency file generation.
1072 if ((A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_M, options::OPT_MM)) ||
1073 (A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_MD)) ||
1074 (A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_MMD))) {
1075 // Determine the output location.
1076 const char *DepFile;
1077 if (Arg *MF = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_MF)) {
1078 DepFile = MF->getValue();
1079 C.addFailureResultFile(DepFile, &JA);
1080 } else if (Output.getType() == types::TY_Dependencies) {
1081 DepFile = Output.getFilename();
1082 } else if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_M) ||
1083 A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_MM)) {
1084 DepFile = "-";
1085 } else {
1086 DepFile = getDependencyFileName(Args, Inputs);
1087 C.addFailureResultFile(DepFile, &JA);
1088 }
1089 CmdArgs.push_back("-dependency-file");
1090 CmdArgs.push_back(DepFile);
1091
1092 // Add a default target if one wasn't specified.
1093 if (!Args.hasArg(options::OPT_MT) && !Args.hasArg(options::OPT_MQ)) {
1094 const char *DepTarget;
1095
1096 // If user provided -o, that is the dependency target, except
1097 // when we are only generating a dependency file.
1098 Arg *OutputOpt = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_o);
1099 if (OutputOpt && Output.getType() != types::TY_Dependencies) {
1100 DepTarget = OutputOpt->getValue();
1101 } else {
1102 // Otherwise derive from the base input.
1103 //
1104 // FIXME: This should use the computed output file location.
1105 SmallString<128> P(Inputs[0].getBaseInput());
1106 llvm::sys::path::replace_extension(P, "o");
1107 DepTarget = Args.MakeArgString(llvm::sys::path::filename(P));
1108 }
1109
1110 if (!A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_MD) && !A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_MMD)) {
1111 CmdArgs.push_back("-w");
1112 }
1113 CmdArgs.push_back("-MT");
1114 SmallString<128> Quoted;
1115 QuoteTarget(DepTarget, Quoted);
1116 CmdArgs.push_back(Args.MakeArgString(Quoted));
1117 }
1118
1119 if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_M) ||
1120 A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_MD))
1121 CmdArgs.push_back("-sys-header-deps");
1122 if ((isa<PrecompileJobAction>(JA) &&
1123 !Args.hasArg(options::OPT_fno_module_file_deps)) ||
1124 Args.hasArg(options::OPT_fmodule_file_deps))
1125 CmdArgs.push_back("-module-file-deps");
1126 }
1127
1128 if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT_MG)) {
1129 if (!A || A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_MD) ||
1130 A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_MMD))
1131 D.Diag(diag::err_drv_mg_requires_m_or_mm);
1132 CmdArgs.push_back("-MG");
1133 }
1134
1135 Args.AddLastArg(CmdArgs, options::OPT_MP);
1136 Args.AddLastArg(CmdArgs, options::OPT_MV);
1137
1138 // Convert all -MQ <target> args to -MT <quoted target>
1139 for (const Arg *A : Args.filtered(options::OPT_MT, options::OPT_MQ)) {
1140 A->claim();
1141
1142 if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_MQ)) {
1143 CmdArgs.push_back("-MT");
1144 SmallString<128> Quoted;
1145 QuoteTarget(A->getValue(), Quoted);
1146 CmdArgs.push_back(Args.MakeArgString(Quoted));
1147
1148 // -MT flag - no change
1149 } else {
1150 A->render(Args, CmdArgs);
1151 }
1152 }
1153
1154 // Add offload include arguments specific for CUDA. This must happen before
1155 // we -I or -include anything else, because we must pick up the CUDA headers
1156 // from the particular CUDA installation, rather than from e.g.
1157 // /usr/local/include.
1158 if (JA.isOffloading(Action::OFK_Cuda))
1159 getToolChain().AddCudaIncludeArgs(Args, CmdArgs);
1160
1161 // If we are offloading to a target via OpenMP we need to include the
1162 // openmp_wrappers folder which contains alternative system headers.
1163 if (JA.isDeviceOffloading(Action::OFK_OpenMP) &&
1164 getToolChain().getTriple().isNVPTX()){
1165 if (!Args.hasArg(options::OPT_nobuiltininc)) {
1166 // Add openmp_wrappers/* to our system include path. This lets us wrap
1167 // standard library headers.
1168 SmallString<128> P(D.ResourceDir);
1169 llvm::sys::path::append(P, "include");
1170 llvm::sys::path::append(P, "openmp_wrappers");
1171 CmdArgs.push_back("-internal-isystem");
1172 CmdArgs.push_back(Args.MakeArgString(P));
1173 }
1174
1175 CmdArgs.push_back("-include");
1176 CmdArgs.push_back("__clang_openmp_math_declares.h");
1177 }
1178
1179 // Add -i* options, and automatically translate to
1180 // -include-pch/-include-pth for transparent PCH support. It's
1181 // wonky, but we include looking for .gch so we can support seamless
1182 // replacement into a build system already set up to be generating
1183 // .gch files.
1184
1185 if (getToolChain().getDriver().IsCLMode()) {
1186 const Arg *YcArg = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT__SLASH_Yc);
1187 const Arg *YuArg = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT__SLASH_Yu);
1188 if (YcArg && JA.getKind() >= Action::PrecompileJobClass &&
1189 JA.getKind() <= Action::AssembleJobClass) {
1190 CmdArgs.push_back(Args.MakeArgString("-building-pch-with-obj"));
1191 }
1192 if (YcArg || YuArg) {
1193 StringRef ThroughHeader = YcArg ? YcArg->getValue() : YuArg->getValue();
1194 if (!isa<PrecompileJobAction>(JA)) {
1195 CmdArgs.push_back("-include-pch");
1196 CmdArgs.push_back(Args.MakeArgString(D.GetClPchPath(
1197 C, !ThroughHeader.empty()
1198 ? ThroughHeader
1199 : llvm::sys::path::filename(Inputs[0].getBaseInput()))));
1200 }
1201
1202 if (ThroughHeader.empty()) {
1203 CmdArgs.push_back(Args.MakeArgString(
1204 Twine("-pch-through-hdrstop-") + (YcArg ? "create" : "use")));
1205 } else {
1206 CmdArgs.push_back(
1207 Args.MakeArgString(Twine("-pch-through-header=") + ThroughHeader));
1208 }
1209 }
1210 }
1211
1212 bool RenderedImplicitInclude = false;
1213 for (const Arg *A : Args.filtered(options::OPT_clang_i_Group)) {
1214 if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_include)) {
1215 // Handling of gcc-style gch precompiled headers.
1216 bool IsFirstImplicitInclude = !RenderedImplicitInclude;
1217 RenderedImplicitInclude = true;
1218
1219 bool FoundPCH = false;
1220 SmallString<128> P(A->getValue());
1221 // We want the files to have a name like foo.h.pch. Add a dummy extension
1222 // so that replace_extension does the right thing.
1223 P += ".dummy";
1224 llvm::sys::path::replace_extension(P, "pch");
1225 if (llvm::sys::fs::exists(P))
1226 FoundPCH = true;
1227
1228 if (!FoundPCH) {
1229 llvm::sys::path::replace_extension(P, "gch");
1230 if (llvm::sys::fs::exists(P)) {
1231 FoundPCH = true;
1232 }
1233 }
1234
1235 if (FoundPCH) {
1236 if (IsFirstImplicitInclude) {
1237 A->claim();
1238 CmdArgs.push_back("-include-pch");
1239 CmdArgs.push_back(Args.MakeArgString(P));
1240 continue;
1241 } else {
1242 // Ignore the PCH if not first on command line and emit warning.
1243 D.Diag(diag::warn_drv_pch_not_first_include) << P
1244 << A->getAsString(Args);
1245 }
1246 }
1247 } else if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_isystem_after)) {
1248 // Handling of paths which must come late. These entries are handled by
1249 // the toolchain itself after the resource dir is inserted in the right
1250 // search order.
1251 // Do not claim the argument so that the use of the argument does not
1252 // silently go unnoticed on toolchains which do not honour the option.
1253 continue;
1254 }
1255
1256 // Not translated, render as usual.
1257 A->claim();
1258 A->render(Args, CmdArgs);
1259 }
1260
1261 Args.AddAllArgs(CmdArgs,
1262 {options::OPT_D, options::OPT_U, options::OPT_I_Group,
1263 options::OPT_F, options::OPT_index_header_map});
1264
1265 // Add -Wp, and -Xpreprocessor if using the preprocessor.
1266
1267 // FIXME: There is a very unfortunate problem here, some troubled
1268 // souls abuse -Wp, to pass preprocessor options in gcc syntax. To
1269 // really support that we would have to parse and then translate
1270 // those options. :(
1271 Args.AddAllArgValues(CmdArgs, options::OPT_Wp_COMMA,
1272 options::OPT_Xpreprocessor);
1273
1274 // -I- is a deprecated GCC feature, reject it.
1275 if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_I_))
1276 D.Diag(diag::err_drv_I_dash_not_supported) << A->getAsString(Args);
1277
1278 // If we have a --sysroot, and don't have an explicit -isysroot flag, add an
1279 // -isysroot to the CC1 invocation.
1280 StringRef sysroot = C.getSysRoot();
1281 if (sysroot != "") {
1282 if (!Args.hasArg(options::OPT_isysroot)) {
1283 CmdArgs.push_back("-isysroot");
1284 CmdArgs.push_back(C.getArgs().MakeArgString(sysroot));
1285 }
1286 }
1287
1288 // Parse additional include paths from environment variables.
1289 // FIXME: We should probably sink the logic for handling these from the
1290 // frontend into the driver. It will allow deleting 4 otherwise unused flags.
1291 // CPATH - included following the user specified includes (but prior to
1292 // builtin and standard includes).
1293 addDirectoryList(Args, CmdArgs, "-I", "CPATH");
1294 // C_INCLUDE_PATH - system includes enabled when compiling C.
1295 addDirectoryList(Args, CmdArgs, "-c-isystem", "C_INCLUDE_PATH");
1296 // CPLUS_INCLUDE_PATH - system includes enabled when compiling C++.
1297 addDirectoryList(Args, CmdArgs, "-cxx-isystem", "CPLUS_INCLUDE_PATH");
1298 // OBJC_INCLUDE_PATH - system includes enabled when compiling ObjC.
1299 addDirectoryList(Args, CmdArgs, "-objc-isystem", "OBJC_INCLUDE_PATH");
1300 // OBJCPLUS_INCLUDE_PATH - system includes enabled when compiling ObjC++.
1301 addDirectoryList(Args, CmdArgs, "-objcxx-isystem", "OBJCPLUS_INCLUDE_PATH");
1302
1303 // While adding the include arguments, we also attempt to retrieve the
1304 // arguments of related offloading toolchains or arguments that are specific
1305 // of an offloading programming model.
1306
1307 // Add C++ include arguments, if needed.
1308 if (types::isCXX(Inputs[0].getType()))
1309 forAllAssociatedToolChains(C, JA, getToolChain(),
1310 [&Args, &CmdArgs](const ToolChain &TC) {
1311 TC.AddClangCXXStdlibIncludeArgs(Args, CmdArgs);
1312 });
1313
1314 // Add system include arguments for all targets but IAMCU.
1315 if (!IsIAMCU)
1316 forAllAssociatedToolChains(C, JA, getToolChain(),
1317 [&Args, &CmdArgs](const ToolChain &TC) {
1318 TC.AddClangSystemIncludeArgs(Args, CmdArgs);
1319 });
1320 else {
1321 // For IAMCU add special include arguments.
1322 getToolChain().AddIAMCUIncludeArgs(Args, CmdArgs);
1323 }
1324}

1390
1391void Clang::AddARMTargetArgs(const llvm::Triple &Triple, const ArgList &Args,
1392 ArgStringList &CmdArgs, bool KernelOrKext) const {
1393 RenderARMABI(Triple, Args, CmdArgs);
1394
1395 // Determine floating point ABI from the options & target defaults.
1396 arm::FloatABI ABI = arm::getARMFloatABI(getToolChain(), Args);
1397 if (ABI == arm::FloatABI::Soft) {
1398 // Floating point operations and argument passing are soft.
1399 // FIXME: This changes CPP defines, we need -target-soft-float.
1400 CmdArgs.push_back("-msoft-float");
1401 CmdArgs.push_back("-mfloat-abi");
1402 CmdArgs.push_back("soft");
1403 } else if (ABI == arm::FloatABI::SoftFP) {
1404 // Floating point operations are hard, but argument passing is soft.
1405 CmdArgs.push_back("-mfloat-abi");
1406 CmdArgs.push_back("soft");
1407 } else {
1408 // Floating point operations and argument passing are hard.
1409 assert(ABI == arm::FloatABI::Hard && "Invalid float abi!");
1410 CmdArgs.push_back("-mfloat-abi");
1411 CmdArgs.push_back("hard");
1412 }
1413
1414 // Forward the -mglobal-merge option for explicit control over the pass.
1415 if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_mglobal_merge,
1416 options::OPT_mno_global_merge)) {
1417 CmdArgs.push_back("-mllvm");
1418 if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_mno_global_merge))
1419 CmdArgs.push_back("-arm-global-merge=false");
1420 else
1421 CmdArgs.push_back("-arm-global-merge=true");
1422 }
1423
1424 if (!Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_mimplicit_float,
1425 options::OPT_mno_implicit_float, true))
1426 CmdArgs.push_back("-no-implicit-float");
1427
1428 if (Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_mcmse))
1429 CmdArgs.push_back("-mcmse");
1430}

1432void Clang::RenderTargetOptions(const llvm::Triple &EffectiveTriple,
1433 const ArgList &Args, bool KernelOrKext,
1434 ArgStringList &CmdArgs,
1435 llvm::Reloc::Model RelocationModel,
1436 const JobAction &JA) const {
1437 const ToolChain &TC = getToolChain();
1438
1439 // Add the target features
1440 getTargetFeatures(TC, EffectiveTriple, Args, CmdArgs, false);
1441
1442 // Add target specific flags.
1443 switch (TC.getArch()) {
1444 default:
1445 break;
1446
1447 case llvm::Triple::arm:
1448 case llvm::Triple::armeb:
1449 case llvm::Triple::thumb:
1450 case llvm::Triple::thumbeb:
1451 // Use the effective triple, which takes into account the deployment target.
1452 AddARMTargetArgs(EffectiveTriple, Args, CmdArgs, KernelOrKext);
1453 CmdArgs.push_back("-fallow-half-arguments-and-returns");
1454 break;
1455
1456 case llvm::Triple::aarch64:
1457 case llvm::Triple::aarch64_be:
1458 AddAArch64TargetArgs(Args, CmdArgs);
1459 CmdArgs.push_back("-fallow-half-arguments-and-returns");
1460 break;
1461 case llvm::Triple::cheri:
1462 case llvm::Triple::mips:
1463 case llvm::Triple::mipsel:
1464 case llvm::Triple::mips64:
1465 case llvm::Triple::mips64el:
1466 Args.ClaimAllArgs(options::OPT_cheri_linker);
1467 AddMIPSTargetArgs(Args, CmdArgs, RelocationModel == llvm::Reloc::Static, JA);
1468 break;
1469
1470 case llvm::Triple::ppc:
1471 case llvm::Triple::ppc64:
1472 case llvm::Triple::ppc64le:
1473 AddPPCTargetArgs(Args, CmdArgs);
1474 break;
1475
1476 case llvm::Triple::riscv32:
1477 case llvm::Triple::riscv64:
1478 AddRISCVTargetArgs(Args, CmdArgs);
1479 break;
1480
1481 case llvm::Triple::sparc:
1482 case llvm::Triple::sparcel:
1483 case llvm::Triple::sparcv9:
1484 AddSparcTargetArgs(Args, CmdArgs);
1485 break;
1486
1487 case llvm::Triple::systemz:
1488 AddSystemZTargetArgs(Args, CmdArgs);
1489 break;
1490
1491 case llvm::Triple::x86:
1492 case llvm::Triple::x86_64:
1493 AddX86TargetArgs(Args, CmdArgs);
1494 break;
1495
1496 case llvm::Triple::lanai:
1497 AddLanaiTargetArgs(Args, CmdArgs);
1498 break;
1499
1500 case llvm::Triple::hexagon:
1501 AddHexagonTargetArgs(Args, CmdArgs);
1502 break;
1503
1504 case llvm::Triple::wasm32:
1505 case llvm::Triple::wasm64:
1506 AddWebAssemblyTargetArgs(Args, CmdArgs);
1507 break;
1508 }
1509}

1511// Parse -mbranch-protection=<protection>[+<protection>]* where
1512// <protection> ::= standard | none | [bti,pac-ret[+b-key,+leaf]*]
1513// Returns a triple of (return address signing Scope, signing key, require
1514// landing pads)
1515static std::tuple<StringRef, StringRef, bool>
1516ParseAArch64BranchProtection(const Driver &D, const ArgList &Args,
1517 const Arg *A) {
1518 StringRef Scope = "none";
1519 StringRef Key = "a_key";
1520 bool IndirectBranches = false;
1521
1522 StringRef Value = A->getValue();
1523 // This maps onto -mbranch-protection=<scope>+<key>
1524
1525 if (Value.equals("standard")) {
1526 Scope = "non-leaf";
1527 Key = "a_key";
1528 IndirectBranches = true;
1529
1530 } else if (!Value.equals("none")) {
1531 SmallVector<StringRef, 4> BranchProtection;
1532 StringRef(A->getValue()).split(BranchProtection, '+');
1533
1534 auto Protection = BranchProtection.begin();
1535 while (Protection != BranchProtection.end()) {
1536 if (Protection->equals("bti"))
1537 IndirectBranches = true;
1538 else if (Protection->equals("pac-ret")) {
1539 Scope = "non-leaf";
1540 while (++Protection != BranchProtection.end()) {
1541 // Inner loop as "leaf" and "b-key" options must only appear attached
1542 // to pac-ret.
1543 if (Protection->equals("leaf"))
1544 Scope = "all";
1545 else if (Protection->equals("b-key"))
1546 Key = "b_key";
1547 else
1548 break;
1549 }
1550 Protection--;
1551 } else
1552 D.Diag(diag::err_invalid_branch_protection)
1553 << *Protection << A->getAsString(Args);
1554 Protection++;
1555 }
1556 }
1557
1558 return std::make_tuple(Scope, Key, IndirectBranches);
1559}

1576
1577void Clang::AddAArch64TargetArgs(const ArgList &Args,
1578 ArgStringList &CmdArgs) const {
1579 const llvm::Triple &Triple = getToolChain().getEffectiveTriple();
1580
1581 if (!Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_mred_zone, options::OPT_mno_red_zone, true) ||
1582 Args.hasArg(options::OPT_mkernel) ||
1583 Args.hasArg(options::OPT_fapple_kext))
1584 CmdArgs.push_back("-disable-red-zone");
1585
1586 if (!Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_mimplicit_float,
1587 options::OPT_mno_implicit_float, true))
1588 CmdArgs.push_back("-no-implicit-float");
1589
1590 RenderAArch64ABI(Triple, Args, CmdArgs);
1591
1592 if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_mfix_cortex_a53_835769,
1593 options::OPT_mno_fix_cortex_a53_835769)) {
1594 CmdArgs.push_back("-mllvm");
1595 if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_mfix_cortex_a53_835769))
1596 CmdArgs.push_back("-aarch64-fix-cortex-a53-835769=1");
1597 else
1598 CmdArgs.push_back("-aarch64-fix-cortex-a53-835769=0");
1599 } else if (Triple.isAndroid()) {
1600 // Enabled A53 errata (835769) workaround by default on android
1601 CmdArgs.push_back("-mllvm");
1602 CmdArgs.push_back("-aarch64-fix-cortex-a53-835769=1");
1603 }
1604
1605 // Forward the -mglobal-merge option for explicit control over the pass.
1606 if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_mglobal_merge,
1607 options::OPT_mno_global_merge)) {
1608 CmdArgs.push_back("-mllvm");
1609 if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_mno_global_merge))
1610 CmdArgs.push_back("-aarch64-enable-global-merge=false");
1611 else
1612 CmdArgs.push_back("-aarch64-enable-global-merge=true");
1613 }
1614
1615 // Enable/disable return address signing and indirect branch targets.
1616 if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_msign_return_address_EQ,
1617 options::OPT_mbranch_protection_EQ)) {
1618
1619 const Driver &D = getToolChain().getDriver();
1620
1621 StringRef Scope, Key;
1622 bool IndirectBranches;
1623
1624 if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_msign_return_address_EQ)) {
1625 Scope = A->getValue();
1626 if (!Scope.equals("none") && !Scope.equals("non-leaf") &&
1627 !Scope.equals("all"))
1628 D.Diag(diag::err_invalid_branch_protection)
1629 << Scope << A->getAsString(Args);
1630 Key = "a_key";
1631 IndirectBranches = false;
1632 } else
1633 std::tie(Scope, Key, IndirectBranches) =
1634 ParseAArch64BranchProtection(D, Args, A);
1635
1636 CmdArgs.push_back(
1637 Args.MakeArgString(Twine("-msign-return-address=") + Scope));
1638 CmdArgs.push_back(
1639 Args.MakeArgString(Twine("-msign-return-address-key=") + Key));
1640 if (IndirectBranches)
1641 CmdArgs.push_back("-mbranch-target-enforce");
1642 }
1643}

1645static void addCheriFlags(const ArgList &Args, ArgStringList &CmdArgs,
1646 StringRef ABIName) {
1647 if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_cheri, options::OPT_cheri_EQ)) {
1648 CmdArgs.push_back("-cheri-size");
1649 if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_cheri))
1650 CmdArgs.push_back("128");
1651 else {
1652 CmdArgs.push_back(Args.MakeArgString(A->getValue()));
1653 }
1654 }
1655
1656 // Add the -cap-table-abi and -cap-tls-abi flags (ignore for non-purecap ABIs)
1657 bool IsCapTable = true;
1658 StringRef DefaultCapTableABI = "pcrel";
1659 if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_cheri_cap_table_abi)) {
1660 StringRef v = A->getValue();
1661 if (ABIName == "purecap") {
1662 CmdArgs.push_back("-mllvm");
1663 CmdArgs.push_back(Args.MakeArgString("-cheri-cap-table-abi=" + v));
1664 }
1665 IsCapTable = v != "legacy";
1666 A->claim();
1667 } else {
1668 // TODO: eventually remove this and drop legacy support
1669 IsCapTable = Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_cheri_cap_table,
1670 options::OPT_no_cheri_cap_table, true);
1671 StringRef ChosenABI = IsCapTable ? DefaultCapTableABI : "legacy";
1672 if (ABIName == "purecap") {
1673 CmdArgs.push_back("-mllvm");
1674 CmdArgs.push_back(
1675 Args.MakeArgString("-cheri-cap-table-abi=" + ChosenABI));
1676 }
1677 }
1678 bool MxCapTable = Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_cheri_large_cap_table,
1679 options::OPT_no_cheri_large_cap_table, false);
1680 if (IsCapTable) {
1681 CmdArgs.push_back("-mllvm");
1682 CmdArgs.push_back(MxCapTable ? "-mxcaptable=true" : "-mxcaptable=false");
1683 }
1684
1685 if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_cheri_cap_tls_abi)) {
1686 StringRef v = A->getValue();
1687 if (ABIName == "purecap") {
1688 CmdArgs.push_back("-mllvm");
1689 CmdArgs.push_back(Args.MakeArgString("-cheri-cap-tls-abi=" + v));
1690 }
1691 A->claim();
1692 }

1694
1695void Clang::AddMIPSTargetArgs(const ArgList &Args,
1696 ArgStringList &CmdArgs,
1697 bool IsNonPic, const JobAction &JA) const {
1698 const Driver &D = getToolChain().getDriver();
1699 StringRef CPUName;
1700 StringRef ABIName;
1701 const llvm::Triple &Triple = getToolChain().getTriple();
1702 mips::getMipsCPUAndABI(Args, Triple, CPUName, ABIName);
1703 if (IsNonPic && ABIName == "purecap" && !isa<PreprocessJobAction>(JA)) {
1704 D.Diag(diag::warn_cheri_purecap_nopic_broken);
1705 }
1706
1707 CmdArgs.push_back("-target-abi");
1708 CmdArgs.push_back(ABIName.data());
1709
1710 // Add warning about calling functions without prototypes in MIPS CHERI
1711 if (Triple.isMIPS() && ABIName == "purecap")
1712 CmdArgs.push_back("-Wmips-cheri-prototypes");
1713
1714 mips::FloatABI ABI = mips::getMipsFloatABI(D, Args);
1715 if (ABI == mips::FloatABI::Soft) {
1716 // Floating point operations and argument passing are soft.
1717 CmdArgs.push_back("-msoft-float");
1718 CmdArgs.push_back("-mfloat-abi");
1719 CmdArgs.push_back("soft");
1720 } else {
1721 // Floating point operations and argument passing are hard.
1722 assert(ABI == mips::FloatABI::Hard && "Invalid float abi!");
1723 CmdArgs.push_back("-mfloat-abi");
1724 CmdArgs.push_back("hard");
1725 }
1726
1727 if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_mxgot, options::OPT_mno_xgot)) {
1728 if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_mxgot)) {
1729 CmdArgs.push_back("-mllvm");
1730 CmdArgs.push_back("-mxgot");
1731 }
1732 }
1733
1734 if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_mldc1_sdc1,
1735 options::OPT_mno_ldc1_sdc1)) {
1736 if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_mno_ldc1_sdc1)) {
1737 CmdArgs.push_back("-mllvm");
1738 CmdArgs.push_back("-mno-ldc1-sdc1");
1739 }
1740 }
1741
1742 if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_mcheck_zero_division,
1743 options::OPT_mno_check_zero_division)) {
1744 if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_mno_check_zero_division)) {
1745 CmdArgs.push_back("-mllvm");
1746 CmdArgs.push_back("-mno-check-zero-division");
1747 }
1748 }
1749
1750 if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_G)) {
1751 StringRef v = A->getValue();
1752 CmdArgs.push_back("-mllvm");
1753 CmdArgs.push_back(Args.MakeArgString("-mips-ssection-threshold=" + v));
1754 A->claim();
1755 }
1756
1757 Arg *GPOpt = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_mgpopt, options::OPT_mno_gpopt);
1758 Arg *ABICalls =
1759 Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_mabicalls, options::OPT_mno_abicalls);
1760
1761 // -mabicalls is the default for many MIPS environments, even with -fno-pic.
1762 // -mgpopt is the default for static, -fno-pic environments but these two
1763 // options conflict. We want to be certain that -mno-abicalls -mgpopt is
1764 // the only case where -mllvm -mgpopt is passed.
1765 // NOTE: We need a warning here or in the backend to warn when -mgpopt is
1766 // passed explicitly when compiling something with -mabicalls
1767 // (implictly) in affect. Currently the warning is in the backend.
1768 //
1769 // When the ABI in use is N64, we also need to determine the PIC mode that
1770 // is in use, as -fno-pic for N64 implies -mno-abicalls.
1771 bool NoABICalls =
1772 ABICalls && ABICalls->getOption().matches(options::OPT_mno_abicalls);
1773
1774 llvm::Reloc::Model RelocationModel;
1775 unsigned PICLevel;
1776 bool IsPIE;
1777 std::tie(RelocationModel, PICLevel, IsPIE) =
1778 ParsePICArgs(getToolChain(), Args);
1779
1780 NoABICalls = NoABICalls ||
1781 (RelocationModel == llvm::Reloc::Static && ABIName == "n64");
1782
1783 bool WantGPOpt = GPOpt && GPOpt->getOption().matches(options::OPT_mgpopt);
1784 // We quietly ignore -mno-gpopt as the backend defaults to -mno-gpopt.
1785 if (NoABICalls && (!GPOpt || WantGPOpt)) {
1786 CmdArgs.push_back("-mllvm");
1787 CmdArgs.push_back("-mgpopt");
1788
1789 Arg *LocalSData = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_mlocal_sdata,
1790 options::OPT_mno_local_sdata);
1791 Arg *ExternSData = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_mextern_sdata,
1792 options::OPT_mno_extern_sdata);
1793 Arg *EmbeddedData = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_membedded_data,
1794 options::OPT_mno_embedded_data);
1795 if (LocalSData) {
1796 CmdArgs.push_back("-mllvm");
1797 if (LocalSData->getOption().matches(options::OPT_mlocal_sdata)) {
1798 CmdArgs.push_back("-mlocal-sdata=1");
1799 } else {
1800 CmdArgs.push_back("-mlocal-sdata=0");
1801 }
1802 LocalSData->claim();
1803 }
1804
1805 if (ExternSData) {
1806 CmdArgs.push_back("-mllvm");
1807 if (ExternSData->getOption().matches(options::OPT_mextern_sdata)) {
1808 CmdArgs.push_back("-mextern-sdata=1");
1809 } else {
1810 CmdArgs.push_back("-mextern-sdata=0");
1811 }
1812 ExternSData->claim();
1813 }
1814
1815 if (EmbeddedData) {
1816 CmdArgs.push_back("-mllvm");
1817 if (EmbeddedData->getOption().matches(options::OPT_membedded_data)) {
1818 CmdArgs.push_back("-membedded-data=1");
1819 } else {
1820 CmdArgs.push_back("-membedded-data=0");
1821 }
1822 EmbeddedData->claim();
1823 }
1824
1825 } else if ((!ABICalls || (!NoABICalls && ABICalls)) && WantGPOpt)
1826 D.Diag(diag::warn_drv_unsupported_gpopt) << (ABICalls ? 0 : 1);
1827
1828 if (GPOpt)
1829 GPOpt->claim();
1830
1831 if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_mcompact_branches_EQ)) {
1832 StringRef Val = StringRef(A->getValue());
1833 if (mips::hasCompactBranches(CPUName)) {
1834 if (Val == "never" || Val == "always" || Val == "optimal") {
1835 CmdArgs.push_back("-mllvm");
1836 CmdArgs.push_back(Args.MakeArgString("-mips-compact-branches=" + Val));
1837 } else
1838 D.Diag(diag::err_drv_unsupported_option_argument)
1839 << A->getOption().getName() << Val;
1840 } else
1841 D.Diag(diag::warn_target_unsupported_compact_branches) << CPUName;
1842 }
1843
1844 if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_mrelax_pic_calls,
1845 options::OPT_mno_relax_pic_calls)) {
1846 if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_mno_relax_pic_calls)) {
1847 CmdArgs.push_back("-mllvm");
1848 CmdArgs.push_back("-mips-jalr-reloc=0");
1849 }
1850 }
1851
1852 addCheriFlags(Args, CmdArgs, ABIName);
1853}
1854
1855void Clang::AddPPCTargetArgs(const ArgList &Args,
1856 ArgStringList &CmdArgs) const {
1857 // Select the ABI to use.
1858 const char *ABIName = nullptr;
1859 if (getToolChain().getTriple().isOSLinux())
1860 switch (getToolChain().getArch()) {
1861 case llvm::Triple::ppc64: {
1862 // When targeting a processor that supports QPX, or if QPX is
1863 // specifically enabled, default to using the ABI that supports QPX (so
1864 // long as it is not specifically disabled).
1865 bool HasQPX = false;
1866 if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_mcpu_EQ))
1867 HasQPX = A->getValue() == StringRef("a2q");
1868 HasQPX = Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_mqpx, options::OPT_mno_qpx, HasQPX);
1869 if (HasQPX) {
1870 ABIName = "elfv1-qpx";
1871 break;
1872 }
1873
1874 ABIName = "elfv1";
1875 break;
1876 }
1877 case llvm::Triple::ppc64le:
1878 ABIName = "elfv2";
1879 break;
1880 default:
1881 break;
1882 }
1883
1884 if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_mabi_EQ))
1885 // The ppc64 linux abis are all "altivec" abis by default. Accept and ignore
1886 // the option if given as we don't have backend support for any targets
1887 // that don't use the altivec abi.
1888 if (StringRef(A->getValue()) != "altivec")
1889 ABIName = A->getValue();
1890
1891 ppc::FloatABI FloatABI =
1892 ppc::getPPCFloatABI(getToolChain().getDriver(), Args);
1893
1894 if (FloatABI == ppc::FloatABI::Soft) {
1895 // Floating point operations and argument passing are soft.
1896 CmdArgs.push_back("-msoft-float");
1897 CmdArgs.push_back("-mfloat-abi");
1898 CmdArgs.push_back("soft");
1899 } else {
1900 // Floating point operations and argument passing are hard.
1901 assert(FloatABI == ppc::FloatABI::Hard && "Invalid float abi!");
1902 CmdArgs.push_back("-mfloat-abi");
1903 CmdArgs.push_back("hard");
1904 }
1905
1906 if (ABIName) {
1907 CmdArgs.push_back("-target-abi");
1908 CmdArgs.push_back(ABIName);
1909 }
1910}

1914 // FIXME: currently defaults to the soft-float ABIs. Will need to be

1924 else
1925 llvm_unreachable("Unexpected triple!");

1928 CmdArgs.push_back(ABIName);

1995 if (Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_miamcu, options::OPT_mno_iamcu, false)) {
1996 CmdArgs.push_back("-mfloat-abi");
1997 CmdArgs.push_back("soft");

2055
2056void Clang::DumpCompilationDatabase(Compilation &C, StringRef Filename,
2057 StringRef Target, const InputInfo &Output,
2058 const InputInfo &Input, const ArgList &Args) const {
2059 // If this is a dry run, do not create the compilation database file.
2060 if (C.getArgs().hasArg(options::OPT__HASH_HASH_HASH))
2061 return;
2062
2063 using llvm::yaml::escape;
2064 const Driver &D = getToolChain().getDriver();
2065
2066 if (!CompilationDatabase) {
2067 std::error_code EC;
2068 auto File = llvm::make_unique<llvm::raw_fd_ostream>(Filename, EC, llvm::sys::fs::F_Text);
2069 if (EC) {
2070 D.Diag(clang::diag::err_drv_compilationdatabase) << Filename
2071 << EC.message();
2072 return;
2073 }
2074 CompilationDatabase = std::move(File);
2075 }
2076 auto &CDB = *CompilationDatabase;
2077 SmallString<128> Buf;
2078 if (llvm::sys::fs::current_path(Buf))
2079 Buf = ".";
2080 CDB << "{ \"directory\": \"" << escape(Buf) << "\"";
2081 CDB << ", \"file\": \"" << escape(Input.getFilename()) << "\"";
2082 CDB << ", \"output\": \"" << escape(Output.getFilename()) << "\"";
2083 CDB << ", \"arguments\": [\"" << escape(D.ClangExecutable) << "\"";
2084 Buf = "-x";
2085 Buf += types::getTypeName(Input.getType());
2086 CDB << ", \"" << escape(Buf) << "\"";
2087 if (!D.SysRoot.empty() && !Args.hasArg(options::OPT__sysroot_EQ)) {
2088 Buf = "--sysroot=";
2089 Buf += D.SysRoot;
2090 CDB << ", \"" << escape(Buf) << "\"";
2091 }
2092 CDB << ", \"" << escape(Input.getFilename()) << "\"";
2093 for (auto &A: Args) {
2094 auto &O = A->getOption();
2095 // Skip language selection, which is positional.
2096 if (O.getID() == options::OPT_x)
2097 continue;
2098 // Skip writing dependency output and the compilation database itself.
2099 if (O.getGroup().isValid() && O.getGroup().getID() == options::OPT_M_Group)
2100 continue;
2101 // Skip inputs.
2102 if (O.getKind() == Option::InputClass)
2103 continue;
2104 // All other arguments are quoted and appended.
2105 ArgStringList ASL;
2106 A->render(Args, ASL);
2107 for (auto &it: ASL)
2108 CDB << ", \"" << escape(it) << "\"";
2109 }
2110 Buf = "--target=";
2111 Buf += Target;
2112 CDB << ", \"" << escape(Buf) << "\"]},\n";
2113}
2114
2115static void CollectArgsForIntegratedAssembler(Compilation &C,
2116 const ArgList &Args,
2117 ArgStringList &CmdArgs,
2118 const Driver &D) {
2119 if (UseRelaxAll(C, Args))
2120 CmdArgs.push_back("-mrelax-all");
2121
2122 // Only default to -mincremental-linker-compatible if we think we are
2123 // targeting the MSVC linker.
2124 bool DefaultIncrementalLinkerCompatible =
2125 C.getDefaultToolChain().getTriple().isWindowsMSVCEnvironment();
2126 if (Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_mincremental_linker_compatible,
2127 options::OPT_mno_incremental_linker_compatible,
2128 DefaultIncrementalLinkerCompatible))
2129 CmdArgs.push_back("-mincremental-linker-compatible");
2130
2131 switch (C.getDefaultToolChain().getArch()) {
2132 case llvm::Triple::arm:
2133 case llvm::Triple::armeb:
2134 case llvm::Triple::thumb:
2135 case llvm::Triple::thumbeb:
2136 if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_mimplicit_it_EQ)) {
2137 StringRef Value = A->getValue();
2138 if (Value == "always" || Value == "never" || Value == "arm" ||
2139 Value == "thumb") {
2140 CmdArgs.push_back("-mllvm");
2141 CmdArgs.push_back(Args.MakeArgString("-arm-implicit-it=" + Value));
2142 } else {
2143 D.Diag(diag::err_drv_unsupported_option_argument)
2144 << A->getOption().getName() << Value;
2145 }
2146 }
2147 break;
2148 default:
2149 break;
2150 }
2151
2152 // When passing -I arguments to the assembler we sometimes need to
2153 // unconditionally take the next argument. For example, when parsing
2154 // '-Wa,-I -Wa,foo' we need to accept the -Wa,foo arg after seeing the
2155 // -Wa,-I arg and when parsing '-Wa,-I,foo' we need to accept the 'foo'
2156 // arg after parsing the '-I' arg.
2157 bool TakeNextArg = false;
2158
2159 bool UseRelaxRelocations = C.getDefaultToolChain().useRelaxRelocations();
2160 bool UseNoExecStack = C.getDefaultToolChain().isNoExecStackDefault();
2161 const char *MipsTargetFeature = nullptr;
2162 for (const Arg *A :
2163 Args.filtered(options::OPT_Wa_COMMA, options::OPT_Xassembler)) {
2164 A->claim();
2165
2166 for (StringRef Value : A->getValues()) {
2167 if (TakeNextArg) {
2168 CmdArgs.push_back(Value.data());
2169 TakeNextArg = false;
2170 continue;
2171 }
2172
2173 if (C.getDefaultToolChain().getTriple().isOSBinFormatCOFF() &&
2174 Value == "-mbig-obj")
2175 continue; // LLVM handles bigobj automatically
2176
2177 switch (C.getDefaultToolChain().getArch()) {
2178 default:
2179 break;
2180 case llvm::Triple::thumb:
2181 case llvm::Triple::thumbeb:
2182 case llvm::Triple::arm:
2183 case llvm::Triple::armeb:
2184 if (Value == "-mthumb")
2185 // -mthumb has already been processed in ComputeLLVMTriple()
2186 // recognize but skip over here.
2187 continue;
2188 break;
2189 case llvm::Triple::mips:
2190 case llvm::Triple::mipsel:
2191 case llvm::Triple::mips64:
2192 case llvm::Triple::mips64el:
2193 case llvm::Triple::cheri:
2194 if (Value == "--trap") {
2195 CmdArgs.push_back("-target-feature");
2196 CmdArgs.push_back("+use-tcc-in-div");
2197 continue;
2198 }
2199 if (Value == "--break") {
2200 CmdArgs.push_back("-target-feature");
2201 CmdArgs.push_back("-use-tcc-in-div");
2202 continue;
2203 }
2204 if (Value.startswith("-msoft-float")) {
2205 CmdArgs.push_back("-target-feature");
2206 CmdArgs.push_back("+soft-float");
2207 continue;
2208 }
2209 if (Value.startswith("-mhard-float")) {
2210 CmdArgs.push_back("-target-feature");
2211 CmdArgs.push_back("-soft-float");
2212 continue;
2213 }
2214
2215 MipsTargetFeature = llvm::StringSwitch<const char *>(Value)
2216 .Case("-mips1", "+mips1")
2217 .Case("-mips2", "+mips2")
2218 .Case("-mips3", "+mips3")
2219 .Case("-mips4", "+mips4")
2220 .Case("-mips5", "+mips5")
2221 .Case("-mips32", "+mips32")
2222 .Case("-mips32r2", "+mips32r2")
2223 .Case("-mips32r3", "+mips32r3")
2224 .Case("-mips32r5", "+mips32r5")
2225 .Case("-mips32r6", "+mips32r6")
2226 .Case("-mips64", "+mips64")
2227 .Case("-mips64r2", "+mips64r2")
2228 .Case("-mips64r3", "+mips64r3")
2229 .Case("-mips64r5", "+mips64r5")
2230 .Case("-mips64r6", "+mips64r6")
2231 .Default(nullptr);
2232 if (MipsTargetFeature)
2233 continue;
2234 }
2235
2236 if (Value == "-force_cpusubtype_ALL") {
2237 // Do nothing, this is the default and we don't support anything else.
2238 } else if (Value == "-L") {
2239 CmdArgs.push_back("-msave-temp-labels");
2240 } else if (Value == "--fatal-warnings") {
2241 CmdArgs.push_back("-massembler-fatal-warnings");
2242 } else if (Value == "--noexecstack") {
2243 UseNoExecStack = true;
2244 } else if (Value.startswith("-compress-debug-sections") ||
2245 Value.startswith("--compress-debug-sections") ||
2246 Value == "-nocompress-debug-sections" ||
2247 Value == "--nocompress-debug-sections") {
2248 CmdArgs.push_back(Value.data());
2249 } else if (Value == "-mrelax-relocations=yes" ||
2250 Value == "--mrelax-relocations=yes") {
2251 UseRelaxRelocations = true;
2252 } else if (Value == "-mrelax-relocations=no" ||
2253 Value == "--mrelax-relocations=no") {
2254 UseRelaxRelocations = false;
2255 } else if (Value.startswith("-I")) {
2256 CmdArgs.push_back(Value.data());
2257 // We need to consume the next argument if the current arg is a plain
2258 // -I. The next arg will be the include directory.
2259 if (Value == "-I")
2260 TakeNextArg = true;
2261 } else if (Value.startswith("-gdwarf-")) {
2262 // "-gdwarf-N" options are not cc1as options.
2263 unsigned DwarfVersion = DwarfVersionNum(Value);
2264 if (DwarfVersion == 0) { // Send it onward, and let cc1as complain.
2265 CmdArgs.push_back(Value.data());
2266 } else {
2267 RenderDebugEnablingArgs(Args, CmdArgs,
2268 codegenoptions::LimitedDebugInfo,
2269 DwarfVersion, llvm::DebuggerKind::Default);
2270 }
2271 } else if (Value.startswith("-mcpu") || Value.startswith("-mfpu") ||
2272 Value.startswith("-mhwdiv") || Value.startswith("-march")) {
2273 // Do nothing, we'll validate it later.
2274 } else if (Value == "-defsym") {
2275 if (A->getNumValues() != 2) {
2276 D.Diag(diag::err_drv_defsym_invalid_format) << Value;
2277 break;
2278 }
2279 const char *S = A->getValue(1);
2280 auto Pair = StringRef(S).split('=');
2281 auto Sym = Pair.first;
2282 auto SVal = Pair.second;
2283
2284 if (Sym.empty() || SVal.empty()) {
2285 D.Diag(diag::err_drv_defsym_invalid_format) << S;
2286 break;
2287 }
2288 int64_t IVal;
2289 if (SVal.getAsInteger(0, IVal)) {
2290 D.Diag(diag::err_drv_defsym_invalid_symval) << SVal;
2291 break;
2292 }
2293 CmdArgs.push_back(Value.data());
2294 TakeNextArg = true;
2295 } else if (Value == "-fdebug-compilation-dir") {
2296 CmdArgs.push_back("-fdebug-compilation-dir");
2297 TakeNextArg = true;
2298 } else {
2299 D.Diag(diag::err_drv_unsupported_option_argument)
2300 << A->getOption().getName() << Value;
2301 }
2302 }
2303 }
2304 if (UseRelaxRelocations)
2305 CmdArgs.push_back("--mrelax-relocations");
2306 if (UseNoExecStack)
2307 CmdArgs.push_back("-mnoexecstack");
2308 if (MipsTargetFeature != nullptr) {
2309 CmdArgs.push_back("-target-feature");
2310 CmdArgs.push_back(MipsTargetFeature);
2311 }
2312
2313 // forward -fembed-bitcode to assmebler
2314 if (C.getDriver().embedBitcodeEnabled() ||
2315 C.getDriver().embedBitcodeMarkerOnly())
2316 Args.AddLastArg(CmdArgs, options::OPT_fembed_bitcode_EQ);
2317}
2318
2319static void RenderFloatingPointOptions(const ToolChain &TC, const Driver &D,
2320 bool OFastEnabled, const ArgList &Args,
2321 ArgStringList &CmdArgs) {
2322 // Handle various floating point optimization flags, mapping them to the
2323 // appropriate LLVM code generation flags. This is complicated by several
2324 // "umbrella" flags, so we do this by stepping through the flags incrementally
2325 // adjusting what we think is enabled/disabled, then at the end setting the
2326 // LLVM flags based on the final state.
2327 bool HonorINFs = true;
2328 bool HonorNaNs = true;
2329 // -fmath-errno is the default on some platforms, e.g. BSD-derived OSes.
2330 bool MathErrno = TC.IsMathErrnoDefault();
2331 bool AssociativeMath = false;
2332 bool ReciprocalMath = false;
2333 bool SignedZeros = true;
2334 bool TrappingMath = true;
2335 StringRef DenormalFPMath = "";
2336 StringRef FPContract = "";
2337
2338 if (const Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_flimited_precision_EQ)) {
2339 CmdArgs.push_back("-mlimit-float-precision");
2340 CmdArgs.push_back(A->getValue());
2341 }
2342
2343 for (const Arg *A : Args) {
2344 switch (A->getOption().getID()) {
2345 // If this isn't an FP option skip the claim below
2346 default: continue;
2347
2348 // Options controlling individual features
2349 case options::OPT_fhonor_infinities: HonorINFs = true; break;
2350 case options::OPT_fno_honor_infinities: HonorINFs = false; break;
2351 case options::OPT_fhonor_nans: HonorNaNs = true; break;
2352 case options::OPT_fno_honor_nans: HonorNaNs = false; break;
2353 case options::OPT_fmath_errno: MathErrno = true; break;
2354 case options::OPT_fno_math_errno: MathErrno = false; break;
2355 case options::OPT_fassociative_math: AssociativeMath = true; break;
2356 case options::OPT_fno_associative_math: AssociativeMath = false; break;
2357 case options::OPT_freciprocal_math: ReciprocalMath = true; break;
2358 case options::OPT_fno_reciprocal_math: ReciprocalMath = false; break;
2359 case options::OPT_fsigned_zeros: SignedZeros = true; break;
2360 case options::OPT_fno_signed_zeros: SignedZeros = false; break;
2361 case options::OPT_ftrapping_math: TrappingMath = true; break;
2362 case options::OPT_fno_trapping_math: TrappingMath = false; break;
2363
2364 case options::OPT_fdenormal_fp_math_EQ:
2365 DenormalFPMath = A->getValue();
2366 break;
2367
2368 // Validate and pass through -fp-contract option.
2369 case options::OPT_ffp_contract: {
2370 StringRef Val = A->getValue();
2371 if (Val == "fast" || Val == "on" || Val == "off")
2372 FPContract = Val;
2373 else
2374 D.Diag(diag::err_drv_unsupported_option_argument)
2375 << A->getOption().getName() << Val;
2376 break;
2377 }
2378
2379 case options::OPT_ffinite_math_only:
2380 HonorINFs = false;
2381 HonorNaNs = false;
2382 break;
2383 case options::OPT_fno_finite_math_only:
2384 HonorINFs = true;
2385 HonorNaNs = true;
2386 break;
2387
2388 case options::OPT_funsafe_math_optimizations:
2389 AssociativeMath = true;
2390 ReciprocalMath = true;
2391 SignedZeros = false;
2392 TrappingMath = false;
2393 break;
2394 case options::OPT_fno_unsafe_math_optimizations:
2395 AssociativeMath = false;
2396 ReciprocalMath = false;
2397 SignedZeros = true;
2398 TrappingMath = true;
2399 // -fno_unsafe_math_optimizations restores default denormal handling
2400 DenormalFPMath = "";
2401 break;
2402
2403 case options::OPT_Ofast:
2404 // If -Ofast is the optimization level, then -ffast-math should be enabled
2405 if (!OFastEnabled)
2406 continue;
2407 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
2408 case options::OPT_ffast_math:
2409 HonorINFs = false;
2410 HonorNaNs = false;
2411 MathErrno = false;
2412 AssociativeMath = true;
2413 ReciprocalMath = true;
2414 SignedZeros = false;
2415 TrappingMath = false;
2416 // If fast-math is set then set the fp-contract mode to fast.
2417 FPContract = "fast";
2418 break;
2419 case options::OPT_fno_fast_math:
2420 HonorINFs = true;
2421 HonorNaNs = true;
2422 // Turning on -ffast-math (with either flag) removes the need for
2423 // MathErrno. However, turning *off* -ffast-math merely restores the
2424 // toolchain default (which may be false).
2425 MathErrno = TC.IsMathErrnoDefault();
2426 AssociativeMath = false;
2427 ReciprocalMath = false;
2428 SignedZeros = true;
2429 TrappingMath = true;
2430 // -fno_fast_math restores default denormal and fpcontract handling
2431 DenormalFPMath = "";
2432 FPContract = "";
2433 break;
2434 }
2435
2436 // If we handled this option claim it
2437 A->claim();
2438 }
2439
2440 if (!HonorINFs)
2441 CmdArgs.push_back("-menable-no-infs");
2442
2443 if (!HonorNaNs)
2444 CmdArgs.push_back("-menable-no-nans");
2445
2446 if (MathErrno)
2447 CmdArgs.push_back("-fmath-errno");
2448
2449 if (!MathErrno && AssociativeMath && ReciprocalMath && !SignedZeros &&
2450 !TrappingMath)
2451 CmdArgs.push_back("-menable-unsafe-fp-math");
2452
2453 if (!SignedZeros)
2454 CmdArgs.push_back("-fno-signed-zeros");
2455
2456 if (AssociativeMath && !SignedZeros && !TrappingMath)
2457 CmdArgs.push_back("-mreassociate");
2458
2459 if (ReciprocalMath)
2460 CmdArgs.push_back("-freciprocal-math");
2461
2462 if (!TrappingMath)
2463 CmdArgs.push_back("-fno-trapping-math");
2464
2465 if (!DenormalFPMath.empty())
2466 CmdArgs.push_back(
2467 Args.MakeArgString("-fdenormal-fp-math=" + DenormalFPMath));
2468
2469 if (!FPContract.empty())
2470 CmdArgs.push_back(Args.MakeArgString("-ffp-contract=" + FPContract));
2471
2472 ParseMRecip(D, Args, CmdArgs);
2473
2474 // -ffast-math enables the __FAST_MATH__ preprocessor macro, but check for the
2475 // individual features enabled by -ffast-math instead of the option itself as
2476 // that's consistent with gcc's behaviour.
2477 if (!HonorINFs && !HonorNaNs && !MathErrno && AssociativeMath &&
2478 ReciprocalMath && !SignedZeros && !TrappingMath)
2479 CmdArgs.push_back("-ffast-math");
2480
2481 // Handle __FINITE_MATH_ONLY__ similarly.
2482 if (!HonorINFs && !HonorNaNs)
2483 CmdArgs.push_back("-ffinite-math-only");
2484
2485 if (const Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_mfpmath_EQ)) {
2486 CmdArgs.push_back("-mfpmath");
2487 CmdArgs.push_back(A->getValue());
2488 }
2489
2490 // Disable a codegen optimization for floating-point casts.
2491 if (Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_fno_strict_float_cast_overflow,
2492 options::OPT_fstrict_float_cast_overflow, false))
2493 CmdArgs.push_back("-fno-strict-float-cast-overflow");
2494}
