2496static void RenderAnalyzerOptions(const ArgList &Args, ArgStringList &CmdArgs,
2497 const llvm::Triple &Triple,
2498 const InputInfo &Input) {
2499 // Enable region store model by default.
2500 CmdArgs.push_back("-analyzer-store=region");
2501
2502 // Treat blocks as analysis entry points.
2503 CmdArgs.push_back("-analyzer-opt-analyze-nested-blocks");
2504
2505 // Add default argument set.
2506 if (!Args.hasArg(options::OPT__analyzer_no_default_checks)) {
2507 CmdArgs.push_back("-analyzer-checker=core");
2508 CmdArgs.push_back("-analyzer-checker=apiModeling");
2509
2510 if (!Triple.isWindowsMSVCEnvironment()) {
2511 CmdArgs.push_back("-analyzer-checker=unix");
2512 } else {
2513 // Enable "unix" checkers that also work on Windows.
2514 CmdArgs.push_back("-analyzer-checker=unix.API");
2515 CmdArgs.push_back("-analyzer-checker=unix.Malloc");
2516 CmdArgs.push_back("-analyzer-checker=unix.MallocSizeof");
2517 CmdArgs.push_back("-analyzer-checker=unix.MismatchedDeallocator");
2518 CmdArgs.push_back("-analyzer-checker=unix.cstring.BadSizeArg");
2519 CmdArgs.push_back("-analyzer-checker=unix.cstring.NullArg");
2520 }
2521
2522 // Disable some unix checkers for PS4.
2523 if (Triple.isPS4CPU()) {
2524 CmdArgs.push_back("-analyzer-disable-checker=unix.API");
2525 CmdArgs.push_back("-analyzer-disable-checker=unix.Vfork");
2526 }
2527
2528 if (Triple.isOSDarwin())
2529 CmdArgs.push_back("-analyzer-checker=osx");
2530
2531 CmdArgs.push_back("-analyzer-checker=deadcode");
2532
2533 if (types::isCXX(Input.getType()))
2534 CmdArgs.push_back("-analyzer-checker=cplusplus");
2535
2536 if (!Triple.isPS4CPU()) {
2537 CmdArgs.push_back("-analyzer-checker=security.insecureAPI.UncheckedReturn");
2538 CmdArgs.push_back("-analyzer-checker=security.insecureAPI.getpw");
2539 CmdArgs.push_back("-analyzer-checker=security.insecureAPI.gets");
2540 CmdArgs.push_back("-analyzer-checker=security.insecureAPI.mktemp");
2541 CmdArgs.push_back("-analyzer-checker=security.insecureAPI.mkstemp");
2542 CmdArgs.push_back("-analyzer-checker=security.insecureAPI.vfork");
2543 }
2544
2545 // Default nullability checks.
2546 CmdArgs.push_back("-analyzer-checker=nullability.NullPassedToNonnull");
2547 CmdArgs.push_back("-analyzer-checker=nullability.NullReturnedFromNonnull");
2548 }
2549
2550 // Set the output format. The default is plist, for (lame) historical reasons.
2551 CmdArgs.push_back("-analyzer-output");
2552 if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT__analyzer_output))
2553 CmdArgs.push_back(A->getValue());
2554 else
2555 CmdArgs.push_back("plist");
2556
2557 // Disable the presentation of standard compiler warnings when using
2558 // --analyze. We only want to show static analyzer diagnostics or frontend
2559 // errors.
2560 CmdArgs.push_back("-w");
2561
2562 // Add -Xanalyzer arguments when running as analyzer.
2563 Args.AddAllArgValues(CmdArgs, options::OPT_Xanalyzer);
2564}

2566static void RenderSSPOptions(const ToolChain &TC, const ArgList &Args,
2567 ArgStringList &CmdArgs, bool KernelOrKext) {
2568 const llvm::Triple &EffectiveTriple = TC.getEffectiveTriple();
2569
2570 // NVPTX doesn't support stack protectors; from the compiler's perspective, it
2571 // doesn't even have a stack!
2572 if (EffectiveTriple.isNVPTX())
2573 return;
2574
2575 // -stack-protector=0 is default.
2576 unsigned StackProtectorLevel = 0;
2577 unsigned DefaultStackProtectorLevel =
2578 TC.GetDefaultStackProtectorLevel(KernelOrKext);
2579
2580 if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_fno_stack_protector,
2581 options::OPT_fstack_protector_all,
2582 options::OPT_fstack_protector_strong,
2583 options::OPT_fstack_protector)) {
2584 if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_fstack_protector))
2585 StackProtectorLevel =
2586 std::max<unsigned>(LangOptions::SSPOn, DefaultStackProtectorLevel);
2587 else if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_fstack_protector_strong))
2588 StackProtectorLevel = LangOptions::SSPStrong;
2589 else if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_fstack_protector_all))
2590 StackProtectorLevel = LangOptions::SSPReq;
2591 } else {
2592 StackProtectorLevel = DefaultStackProtectorLevel;
2593 }
2594
2595 if (StackProtectorLevel) {
2596 CmdArgs.push_back("-stack-protector");
2597 CmdArgs.push_back(Args.MakeArgString(Twine(StackProtectorLevel)));
2598 }
2599
2600 // --param ssp-buffer-size=
2601 for (const Arg *A : Args.filtered(options::OPT__param)) {
2602 StringRef Str(A->getValue());
2603 if (Str.startswith("ssp-buffer-size=")) {
2604 if (StackProtectorLevel) {
2605 CmdArgs.push_back("-stack-protector-buffer-size");
2606 // FIXME: Verify the argument is a valid integer.
2607 CmdArgs.push_back(Args.MakeArgString(Str.drop_front(16)));
2608 }
2609 A->claim();
2610 }
2611 }
2612}

2614static void RenderTrivialAutoVarInitOptions(const Driver &D,
2615 const ToolChain &TC,
2616 const ArgList &Args,
2617 ArgStringList &CmdArgs) {
2618 auto DefaultTrivialAutoVarInit = TC.GetDefaultTrivialAutoVarInit();
2619 StringRef TrivialAutoVarInit = "";
2620
2621 for (const Arg *A : Args) {
2622 switch (A->getOption().getID()) {
2623 default:
2624 continue;
2625 case options::OPT_ftrivial_auto_var_init: {
2626 A->claim();
2627 StringRef Val = A->getValue();
2628 if (Val == "uninitialized" || Val == "zero" || Val == "pattern")
2629 TrivialAutoVarInit = Val;
2630 else
2631 D.Diag(diag::err_drv_unsupported_option_argument)
2632 << A->getOption().getName() << Val;
2633 break;
2634 }
2635 }
2636 }
2637
2638 if (TrivialAutoVarInit.empty())
2639 switch (DefaultTrivialAutoVarInit) {
2640 case LangOptions::TrivialAutoVarInitKind::Uninitialized:
2641 break;
2642 case LangOptions::TrivialAutoVarInitKind::Pattern:
2643 TrivialAutoVarInit = "pattern";
2644 break;
2645 case LangOptions::TrivialAutoVarInitKind::Zero:
2646 TrivialAutoVarInit = "zero";
2647 break;
2648 }
2649
2650 if (!TrivialAutoVarInit.empty()) {
2651 if (TrivialAutoVarInit == "zero" && !Args.hasArg(options::OPT_enable_trivial_var_init_zero))
2652 D.Diag(diag::err_drv_trivial_auto_var_init_zero_disabled);
2653 CmdArgs.push_back(
2654 Args.MakeArgString("-ftrivial-auto-var-init=" + TrivialAutoVarInit));
2655 }
2656}

2756static void RenderBuiltinOptions(const ToolChain &TC, const llvm::Triple &T,
2757 const ArgList &Args, ArgStringList &CmdArgs) {
2758 // -fbuiltin is default unless -mkernel is used.
2759 bool UseBuiltins =
2760 Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_fbuiltin, options::OPT_fno_builtin,
2761 !Args.hasArg(options::OPT_mkernel));
2762 if (!UseBuiltins)
2763 CmdArgs.push_back("-fno-builtin");
2764
2765 // -ffreestanding implies -fno-builtin.
2766 if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT_ffreestanding))
2767 UseBuiltins = false;
2768
2769 // Process the -fno-builtin-* options.
2770 for (const auto &Arg : Args) {
2771 const Option &O = Arg->getOption();
2772 if (!O.matches(options::OPT_fno_builtin_))
2773 continue;
2774
2775 Arg->claim();
2776
2777 // If -fno-builtin is specified, then there's no need to pass the option to
2778 // the frontend.
2779 if (!UseBuiltins)
2780 continue;
2781
2782 StringRef FuncName = Arg->getValue();
2783 CmdArgs.push_back(Args.MakeArgString("-fno-builtin-" + FuncName));
2784 }
2785
2786 // le32-specific flags:
2787 // -fno-math-builtin: clang should not convert math builtins to intrinsics
2788 // by default.
2789 if (TC.getArch() == llvm::Triple::le32)
2790 CmdArgs.push_back("-fno-math-builtin");
2791}

2797 llvm::sys::path::append(Result, "ModuleCache");
2798}
2799
2800static void RenderModulesOptions(Compilation &C, const Driver &D,
2801 const ArgList &Args, const InputInfo &Input,
2802 const InputInfo &Output,
2803 ArgStringList &CmdArgs, bool &HaveModules) {
2804 // -fmodules enables the use of precompiled modules (off by default).
2805 // Users can pass -fno-cxx-modules to turn off modules support for
2806 // C++/Objective-C++ programs.
2807 bool HaveClangModules = false;
2808 if (Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_fmodules, options::OPT_fno_modules, false)) {
2809 bool AllowedInCXX = Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_fcxx_modules,
2810 options::OPT_fno_cxx_modules, true);
2811 if (AllowedInCXX || !types::isCXX(Input.getType())) {
2812 CmdArgs.push_back("-fmodules");
2813 HaveClangModules = true;
2814 }
2815 }
2816
2817 HaveModules |= HaveClangModules;
2818 if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT_fmodules_ts)) {
2819 CmdArgs.push_back("-fmodules-ts");
2820 HaveModules = true;
2821 }
2822
2823 // -fmodule-maps enables implicit reading of module map files. By default,
2824 // this is enabled if we are using Clang's flavor of precompiled modules.
2825 if (Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_fimplicit_module_maps,
2826 options::OPT_fno_implicit_module_maps, HaveClangModules))
2827 CmdArgs.push_back("-fimplicit-module-maps");
2828
2829 // -fmodules-decluse checks that modules used are declared so (off by default)
2830 if (Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_fmodules_decluse,
2831 options::OPT_fno_modules_decluse, false))
2832 CmdArgs.push_back("-fmodules-decluse");
2833
2834 // -fmodules-strict-decluse is like -fmodule-decluse, but also checks that
2835 // all #included headers are part of modules.
2836 if (Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_fmodules_strict_decluse,
2837 options::OPT_fno_modules_strict_decluse, false))
2838 CmdArgs.push_back("-fmodules-strict-decluse");
2839
2840 // -fno-implicit-modules turns off implicitly compiling modules on demand.
2841 bool ImplicitModules = false;
2842 if (!Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_fimplicit_modules,
2843 options::OPT_fno_implicit_modules, HaveClangModules)) {
2844 if (HaveModules)
2845 CmdArgs.push_back("-fno-implicit-modules");
2846 } else if (HaveModules) {
2847 ImplicitModules = true;
2848 // -fmodule-cache-path specifies where our implicitly-built module files
2849 // should be written.
2850 SmallString<128> Path;
2851 if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_fmodules_cache_path))
2852 Path = A->getValue();
2853
2854 if (C.isForDiagnostics()) {
2855 // When generating crash reports, we want to emit the modules along with
2856 // the reproduction sources, so we ignore any provided module path.
2857 Path = Output.getFilename();
2858 llvm::sys::path::replace_extension(Path, ".cache");
2859 llvm::sys::path::append(Path, "modules");
2860 } else if (Path.empty()) {
2861 // No module path was provided: use the default.
2862 Driver::getDefaultModuleCachePath(Path);
2863 }
2864
2865 const char Arg[] = "-fmodules-cache-path=";
2866 Path.insert(Path.begin(), Arg, Arg + strlen(Arg));
2867 CmdArgs.push_back(Args.MakeArgString(Path));
2868 }
2869
2870 if (HaveModules) {
2871 // -fprebuilt-module-path specifies where to load the prebuilt module files.
2872 for (const Arg *A : Args.filtered(options::OPT_fprebuilt_module_path)) {
2873 CmdArgs.push_back(Args.MakeArgString(
2874 std::string("-fprebuilt-module-path=") + A->getValue()));
2875 A->claim();
2876 }
2877 }
2878
2879 // -fmodule-name specifies the module that is currently being built (or
2880 // used for header checking by -fmodule-maps).
2881 Args.AddLastArg(CmdArgs, options::OPT_fmodule_name_EQ);
2882
2883 // -fmodule-map-file can be used to specify files containing module
2884 // definitions.
2885 Args.AddAllArgs(CmdArgs, options::OPT_fmodule_map_file);
2886
2887 // -fbuiltin-module-map can be used to load the clang
2888 // builtin headers modulemap file.
2889 if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT_fbuiltin_module_map)) {
2890 SmallString<128> BuiltinModuleMap(D.ResourceDir);
2891 llvm::sys::path::append(BuiltinModuleMap, "include");
2892 llvm::sys::path::append(BuiltinModuleMap, "module.modulemap");
2893 if (llvm::sys::fs::exists(BuiltinModuleMap))
2894 CmdArgs.push_back(
2895 Args.MakeArgString("-fmodule-map-file=" + BuiltinModuleMap));
2896 }
2897
2898 // The -fmodule-file=<name>=<file> form specifies the mapping of module
2899 // names to precompiled module files (the module is loaded only if used).
2900 // The -fmodule-file=<file> form can be used to unconditionally load
2901 // precompiled module files (whether used or not).
2902 if (HaveModules)
2903 Args.AddAllArgs(CmdArgs, options::OPT_fmodule_file);
2904 else
2905 Args.ClaimAllArgs(options::OPT_fmodule_file);
2906
2907 // When building modules and generating crashdumps, we need to dump a module
2908 // dependency VFS alongside the output.
2909 if (HaveClangModules && C.isForDiagnostics()) {
2910 SmallString<128> VFSDir(Output.getFilename());
2911 llvm::sys::path::replace_extension(VFSDir, ".cache");
2912 // Add the cache directory as a temp so the crash diagnostics pick it up.
2913 C.addTempFile(Args.MakeArgString(VFSDir));
2914
2915 llvm::sys::path::append(VFSDir, "vfs");
2916 CmdArgs.push_back("-module-dependency-dir");
2917 CmdArgs.push_back(Args.MakeArgString(VFSDir));
2918 }
2919
2920 if (HaveClangModules)
2921 Args.AddLastArg(CmdArgs, options::OPT_fmodules_user_build_path);
2922
2923 // Pass through all -fmodules-ignore-macro arguments.
2924 Args.AddAllArgs(CmdArgs, options::OPT_fmodules_ignore_macro);
2925 Args.AddLastArg(CmdArgs, options::OPT_fmodules_prune_interval);
2926 Args.AddLastArg(CmdArgs, options::OPT_fmodules_prune_after);
2927
2928 Args.AddLastArg(CmdArgs, options::OPT_fbuild_session_timestamp);
2929
2930 if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_fbuild_session_file)) {
2931 if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT_fbuild_session_timestamp))
2932 D.Diag(diag::err_drv_argument_not_allowed_with)
2933 << A->getAsString(Args) << "-fbuild-session-timestamp";
2934
2935 llvm::sys::fs::file_status Status;
2936 if (llvm::sys::fs::status(A->getValue(), Status))
2937 D.Diag(diag::err_drv_no_such_file) << A->getValue();
2938 CmdArgs.push_back(
2939 Args.MakeArgString("-fbuild-session-timestamp=" +
2940 Twine((uint64_t)Status.getLastModificationTime()
2941 .time_since_epoch()
2942 .count())));
2943 }
2944
2945 if (Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_fmodules_validate_once_per_build_session)) {
2946 if (!Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_fbuild_session_timestamp,
2947 options::OPT_fbuild_session_file))
2948 D.Diag(diag::err_drv_modules_validate_once_requires_timestamp);
2949
2950 Args.AddLastArg(CmdArgs,
2951 options::OPT_fmodules_validate_once_per_build_session);
2952 }
2953
2954 if (Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_fmodules_validate_system_headers,
2955 options::OPT_fno_modules_validate_system_headers,
2956 ImplicitModules))
2957 CmdArgs.push_back("-fmodules-validate-system-headers");
2958
2959 Args.AddLastArg(CmdArgs, options::OPT_fmodules_disable_diagnostic_validation);
2960}

2962static void RenderCharacterOptions(const ArgList &Args, const llvm::Triple &T,

2999static void RenderObjCOptions(const ToolChain &TC, const Driver &D,
3000 const llvm::Triple &T, const ArgList &Args,
3001 ObjCRuntime &Runtime, bool InferCovariantReturns,
3002 const InputInfo &Input, ArgStringList &CmdArgs) {
3003 const llvm::Triple::ArchType Arch = TC.getArch();
3004
3005 // -fobjc-dispatch-method is only relevant with the nonfragile-abi, and legacy
3006 // is the default. Except for deployment target of 10.5, next runtime is
3007 // always legacy dispatch and -fno-objc-legacy-dispatch gets ignored silently.
3008 if (Runtime.isNonFragile()) {
3009 if (!Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_fobjc_legacy_dispatch,
3010 options::OPT_fno_objc_legacy_dispatch,
3011 Runtime.isLegacyDispatchDefaultForArch(Arch))) {
3012 if (TC.UseObjCMixedDispatch())
3013 CmdArgs.push_back("-fobjc-dispatch-method=mixed");
3014 else
3015 CmdArgs.push_back("-fobjc-dispatch-method=non-legacy");
3016 }
3017 }
3018
3019 // When ObjectiveC legacy runtime is in effect on MacOSX, turn on the option
3020 // to do Array/Dictionary subscripting by default.
3021 if (Arch == llvm::Triple::x86 && T.isMacOSX() &&
3022 Runtime.getKind() == ObjCRuntime::FragileMacOSX && Runtime.isNeXTFamily())
3023 CmdArgs.push_back("-fobjc-subscripting-legacy-runtime");
3024
3025 // Allow -fno-objc-arr to trump -fobjc-arr/-fobjc-arc.
3026 // NOTE: This logic is duplicated in ToolChains.cpp.
3027 if (isObjCAutoRefCount(Args)) {
3028 TC.CheckObjCARC();
3029
3030 CmdArgs.push_back("-fobjc-arc");
3031
3032 // FIXME: It seems like this entire block, and several around it should be
3033 // wrapped in isObjC, but for now we just use it here as this is where it
3034 // was being used previously.
3035 if (types::isCXX(Input.getType()) && types::isObjC(Input.getType())) {
3036 if (TC.GetCXXStdlibType(Args) == ToolChain::CST_Libcxx)
3037 CmdArgs.push_back("-fobjc-arc-cxxlib=libc++");
3038 else
3039 CmdArgs.push_back("-fobjc-arc-cxxlib=libstdc++");
3040 }
3041
3042 // Allow the user to enable full exceptions code emission.
3043 // We default off for Objective-C, on for Objective-C++.
3044 if (Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_fobjc_arc_exceptions,
3045 options::OPT_fno_objc_arc_exceptions,
3046 /*default=*/types::isCXX(Input.getType())))
3047 CmdArgs.push_back("-fobjc-arc-exceptions");
3048 }
3049
3050 // Silence warning for full exception code emission options when explicitly
3051 // set to use no ARC.
3052 if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT_fno_objc_arc)) {
3053 Args.ClaimAllArgs(options::OPT_fobjc_arc_exceptions);
3054 Args.ClaimAllArgs(options::OPT_fno_objc_arc_exceptions);
3055 }
3056
3057 // Allow the user to control whether messages can be converted to runtime
3058 // functions.
3059 if (types::isObjC(Input.getType())) {
3060 auto *Arg = Args.getLastArg(
3061 options::OPT_fobjc_convert_messages_to_runtime_calls,
3062 options::OPT_fno_objc_convert_messages_to_runtime_calls);
3063 if (Arg &&
3064 Arg->getOption().matches(
3065 options::OPT_fno_objc_convert_messages_to_runtime_calls))
3066 CmdArgs.push_back("-fno-objc-convert-messages-to-runtime-calls");
3067 }
3068
3069 // -fobjc-infer-related-result-type is the default, except in the Objective-C
3070 // rewriter.
3071 if (InferCovariantReturns)
3072 CmdArgs.push_back("-fno-objc-infer-related-result-type");
3073
3074 // Pass down -fobjc-weak or -fno-objc-weak if present.
3075 if (types::isObjC(Input.getType())) {
3076 auto WeakArg =
3077 Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_fobjc_weak, options::OPT_fno_objc_weak);
3078 if (!WeakArg) {
3079 // nothing to do
3080 } else if (!Runtime.allowsWeak()) {
3081 if (WeakArg->getOption().matches(options::OPT_fobjc_weak))
3082 D.Diag(diag::err_objc_weak_unsupported);
3083 } else {
3084 WeakArg->render(Args, CmdArgs);
3085 }
3086 }
3087}

3095 options::OPT__SLASH_diagnostics_column,
3096 options::OPT__SLASH_diagnostics_caret)) {

3099 CaretDefault = true;
3100 ColumnDefault = true;
3101 break;
3102 case options::OPT__SLASH_diagnostics_column:
3103 CaretDefault = false;
3104 ColumnDefault = true;
3105 break;
3106 case options::OPT__SLASH_diagnostics_classic:
3107 CaretDefault = false;
3108 ColumnDefault = false;
3109 break;

3119 if (!Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_fdiagnostics_fixit_info,
3120 options::OPT_fno_diagnostics_fixit_info))
3121 CmdArgs.push_back("-fno-diagnostics-fixit-info");

3141 std::string("-fdiagnostics-hotness-threshold=") + A->getValue();
3142 CmdArgs.push_back(Args.MakeArgString(Opt));

3204enum class DwarfFissionKind { None, Split, Single };
3205
3206static DwarfFissionKind getDebugFissionKind(const Driver &D,
3207 const ArgList &Args, Arg *&Arg) {
3208 Arg =
3209 Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_gsplit_dwarf, options::OPT_gsplit_dwarf_EQ);
3210 if (!Arg)
3211 return DwarfFissionKind::None;
3212
3213 if (Arg->getOption().matches(options::OPT_gsplit_dwarf))
3214 return DwarfFissionKind::Split;
3215
3216 StringRef Value = Arg->getValue();
3217 if (Value == "split")
3218 return DwarfFissionKind::Split;
3219 if (Value == "single")
3220 return DwarfFissionKind::Single;
3221
3222 D.Diag(diag::err_drv_unsupported_option_argument)
3223 << Arg->getOption().getName() << Arg->getValue();
3224 return DwarfFissionKind::None;
3225}
3226
3227static void RenderDebugOptions(const ToolChain &TC, const Driver &D,
3228 const llvm::Triple &T, const ArgList &Args,
3229 bool EmitCodeView, bool IsWindowsMSVC,
3230 ArgStringList &CmdArgs,
3231 codegenoptions::DebugInfoKind &DebugInfoKind,
3232 DwarfFissionKind &DwarfFission) {
3233 if (Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_fdebug_info_for_profiling,
3234 options::OPT_fno_debug_info_for_profiling, false) &&
3235 checkDebugInfoOption(
3236 Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_fdebug_info_for_profiling), Args, D, TC))
3237 CmdArgs.push_back("-fdebug-info-for-profiling");
3238
3239 // The 'g' groups options involve a somewhat intricate sequence of decisions
3240 // about what to pass from the driver to the frontend, but by the time they
3241 // reach cc1 they've been factored into three well-defined orthogonal choices:
3242 // * what level of debug info to generate
3243 // * what dwarf version to write
3244 // * what debugger tuning to use
3245 // This avoids having to monkey around further in cc1 other than to disable
3246 // codeview if not running in a Windows environment. Perhaps even that
3247 // decision should be made in the driver as well though.
3248 unsigned DWARFVersion = 0;
3249 llvm::DebuggerKind DebuggerTuning = TC.getDefaultDebuggerTuning();
3250
3251 bool SplitDWARFInlining =
3252 Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_fsplit_dwarf_inlining,
3253 options::OPT_fno_split_dwarf_inlining, true);
3254
3255 Args.ClaimAllArgs(options::OPT_g_Group);
3256
3257 Arg* SplitDWARFArg;
3258 DwarfFission = getDebugFissionKind(D, Args, SplitDWARFArg);
3259
3260 if (DwarfFission != DwarfFissionKind::None &&
3261 !checkDebugInfoOption(SplitDWARFArg, Args, D, TC)) {
3262 DwarfFission = DwarfFissionKind::None;
3263 SplitDWARFInlining = false;
3264 }
3265
3266 if (const Arg *A =
3267 Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_g_Group, options::OPT_gsplit_dwarf,
3268 options::OPT_gsplit_dwarf_EQ)) {
3269 DebugInfoKind = codegenoptions::LimitedDebugInfo;
3270
3271 // If the last option explicitly specified a debug-info level, use it.
3272 if (checkDebugInfoOption(A, Args, D, TC) &&
3273 A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_gN_Group)) {
3274 DebugInfoKind = DebugLevelToInfoKind(*A);
3275 // For -g0 or -gline-tables-only, drop -gsplit-dwarf. This gets a bit more
3276 // complicated if you've disabled inline info in the skeleton CUs
3277 // (SplitDWARFInlining) - then there's value in composing split-dwarf and
3278 // line-tables-only, so let those compose naturally in that case.
3279 if (DebugInfoKind == codegenoptions::NoDebugInfo ||
3280 DebugInfoKind == codegenoptions::DebugDirectivesOnly ||
3281 (DebugInfoKind == codegenoptions::DebugLineTablesOnly &&
3282 SplitDWARFInlining))
3283 DwarfFission = DwarfFissionKind::None;
3284 }
3285 }
3286
3287 // If a debugger tuning argument appeared, remember it.
3288 if (const Arg *A =
3289 Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_gTune_Group, options::OPT_ggdbN_Group)) {
3290 if (checkDebugInfoOption(A, Args, D, TC)) {
3291 if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_glldb))
3292 DebuggerTuning = llvm::DebuggerKind::LLDB;
3293 else if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_gsce))
3294 DebuggerTuning = llvm::DebuggerKind::SCE;
3295 else
3296 DebuggerTuning = llvm::DebuggerKind::GDB;
3297 }
3298 }
3299
3300 // If a -gdwarf argument appeared, remember it.
3301 if (const Arg *A =
3302 Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_gdwarf_2, options::OPT_gdwarf_3,
3303 options::OPT_gdwarf_4, options::OPT_gdwarf_5))
3304 if (checkDebugInfoOption(A, Args, D, TC))
3305 DWARFVersion = DwarfVersionNum(A->getSpelling());
3306
3307 if (const Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_gcodeview)) {
3308 if (checkDebugInfoOption(A, Args, D, TC))
3309 EmitCodeView = true;
3310 }
3311
3312 // If the user asked for debug info but did not explicitly specify -gcodeview
3313 // or -gdwarf, ask the toolchain for the default format.
3314 if (!EmitCodeView && DWARFVersion == 0 &&
3315 DebugInfoKind != codegenoptions::NoDebugInfo) {
3316 switch (TC.getDefaultDebugFormat()) {
3317 case codegenoptions::DIF_CodeView:
3318 EmitCodeView = true;
3319 break;
3320 case codegenoptions::DIF_DWARF:
3321 DWARFVersion = TC.GetDefaultDwarfVersion();
3322 break;
3323 }
3324 }
3325
3326 // -gline-directives-only supported only for the DWARF debug info.
3327 if (DWARFVersion == 0 && DebugInfoKind == codegenoptions::DebugDirectivesOnly)
3328 DebugInfoKind = codegenoptions::NoDebugInfo;
3329
3330 // We ignore flag -gstrict-dwarf for now.
3331 // And we handle flag -grecord-gcc-switches later with DWARFDebugFlags.
3332 Args.ClaimAllArgs(options::OPT_g_flags_Group);
3333
3334 // Column info is included by default for everything except SCE and
3335 // CodeView. Clang doesn't track end columns, just starting columns, which,
3336 // in theory, is fine for CodeView (and PDB). In practice, however, the
3337 // Microsoft debuggers don't handle missing end columns well, so it's better
3338 // not to include any column info.
3339 if (const Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_gcolumn_info))
3340 (void)checkDebugInfoOption(A, Args, D, TC);
3341 if (Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_gcolumn_info, options::OPT_gno_column_info,
3342 /*Default=*/!EmitCodeView &&
3343 DebuggerTuning != llvm::DebuggerKind::SCE))
3344 CmdArgs.push_back("-dwarf-column-info");
3345
3346 // FIXME: Move backend command line options to the module.
3347 // If -gline-tables-only or -gline-directives-only is the last option it wins.
3348 if (const Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_gmodules))
3349 if (checkDebugInfoOption(A, Args, D, TC)) {
3350 if (DebugInfoKind != codegenoptions::DebugLineTablesOnly &&
3351 DebugInfoKind != codegenoptions::DebugDirectivesOnly) {
3352 DebugInfoKind = codegenoptions::LimitedDebugInfo;
3353 CmdArgs.push_back("-dwarf-ext-refs");
3354 CmdArgs.push_back("-fmodule-format=obj");
3355 }
3356 }
3357
3358 // -gsplit-dwarf enables the backend dwarf splitting and extraction.
3359 if (T.isOSBinFormatELF()) {
3360 if (!SplitDWARFInlining)
3361 CmdArgs.push_back("-fno-split-dwarf-inlining");
3362
3363 if (DwarfFission != DwarfFissionKind::None) {
3364 if (DwarfFission == DwarfFissionKind::Single)
3365 CmdArgs.push_back("-enable-split-dwarf=single");
3366 else
3367 CmdArgs.push_back("-enable-split-dwarf");
3368 }
3369 }
3370
3371 // After we've dealt with all combinations of things that could
3372 // make DebugInfoKind be other than None or DebugLineTablesOnly,
3373 // figure out if we need to "upgrade" it to standalone debug info.
3374 // We parse these two '-f' options whether or not they will be used,
3375 // to claim them even if you wrote "-fstandalone-debug -gline-tables-only"
3376 bool NeedFullDebug = Args.hasFlag(
3377 options::OPT_fstandalone_debug, options::OPT_fno_standalone_debug,
3378 DebuggerTuning == llvm::DebuggerKind::LLDB ||
3379 TC.GetDefaultStandaloneDebug());
3380 if (const Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_fstandalone_debug))
3381 (void)checkDebugInfoOption(A, Args, D, TC);
3382 if (DebugInfoKind == codegenoptions::LimitedDebugInfo && NeedFullDebug)
3383 DebugInfoKind = codegenoptions::FullDebugInfo;
3384
3385 if (Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_gembed_source, options::OPT_gno_embed_source,
3386 false)) {
3387 // Source embedding is a vendor extension to DWARF v5. By now we have
3388 // checked if a DWARF version was stated explicitly, and have otherwise
3389 // fallen back to the target default, so if this is still not at least 5
3390 // we emit an error.
3391 const Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_gembed_source);
3392 if (DWARFVersion < 5)
3393 D.Diag(diag::err_drv_argument_only_allowed_with)
3394 << A->getAsString(Args) << "-gdwarf-5";
3395 else if (checkDebugInfoOption(A, Args, D, TC))
3396 CmdArgs.push_back("-gembed-source");
3397 }
3398
3399 if (EmitCodeView) {
3400 CmdArgs.push_back("-gcodeview");
3401
3402 // Emit codeview type hashes if requested.
3403 if (Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_gcodeview_ghash,
3404 options::OPT_gno_codeview_ghash, false)) {
3405 CmdArgs.push_back("-gcodeview-ghash");
3406 }
3407 }
3408
3409 // Adjust the debug info kind for the given toolchain.
3410 TC.adjustDebugInfoKind(DebugInfoKind, Args);
3411
3412 RenderDebugEnablingArgs(Args, CmdArgs, DebugInfoKind, DWARFVersion,
3413 DebuggerTuning);
3414
3415 // -fdebug-macro turns on macro debug info generation.
3416 if (Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_fdebug_macro, options::OPT_fno_debug_macro,
3417 false))
3418 if (checkDebugInfoOption(Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_fdebug_macro), Args,
3419 D, TC))
3420 CmdArgs.push_back("-debug-info-macro");
3421
3422 // -ggnu-pubnames turns on gnu style pubnames in the backend.
3423 const auto *PubnamesArg =
3424 Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_ggnu_pubnames, options::OPT_gno_gnu_pubnames,
3425 options::OPT_gpubnames, options::OPT_gno_pubnames);
3426 if (DwarfFission != DwarfFissionKind::None ||
3427 DebuggerTuning == llvm::DebuggerKind::LLDB ||
3428 (PubnamesArg && checkDebugInfoOption(PubnamesArg, Args, D, TC)))
3429 if (!PubnamesArg ||
3430 (!PubnamesArg->getOption().matches(options::OPT_gno_gnu_pubnames) &&
3431 !PubnamesArg->getOption().matches(options::OPT_gno_pubnames)))
3432 CmdArgs.push_back(PubnamesArg && PubnamesArg->getOption().matches(
3433 options::OPT_gpubnames)
3434 ? "-gpubnames"
3435 : "-ggnu-pubnames");
3436
3437 if (Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_fdebug_ranges_base_address,
3438 options::OPT_fno_debug_ranges_base_address, false)) {
3439 CmdArgs.push_back("-fdebug-ranges-base-address");
3440 }
3441
3442 // -gdwarf-aranges turns on the emission of the aranges section in the
3443 // backend.
3444 // Always enabled for SCE tuning.
3445 bool NeedAranges = DebuggerTuning == llvm::DebuggerKind::SCE;
3446 if (const Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_gdwarf_aranges))
3447 NeedAranges = checkDebugInfoOption(A, Args, D, TC) || NeedAranges;
3448 if (NeedAranges) {
3449 CmdArgs.push_back("-mllvm");
3450 CmdArgs.push_back("-generate-arange-section");
3451 }
3452
3453 if (Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_fdebug_types_section,
3454 options::OPT_fno_debug_types_section, false)) {
3455 if (!T.isOSBinFormatELF()) {
3456 D.Diag(diag::err_drv_unsupported_opt_for_target)
3457 << Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_fdebug_types_section)
3458 ->getAsString(Args)
3459 << T.getTriple();
3460 } else if (checkDebugInfoOption(
3461 Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_fdebug_types_section), Args, D,
3462 TC)) {
3463 CmdArgs.push_back("-mllvm");
3464 CmdArgs.push_back("-generate-type-units");
3465 }
3466 }
3467
3468 // Decide how to render forward declarations of template instantiations.
3469 // SCE wants full descriptions, others just get them in the name.
3470 if (DebuggerTuning == llvm::DebuggerKind::SCE)
3471 CmdArgs.push_back("-debug-forward-template-params");
3472
3473 // Do we need to explicitly import anonymous namespaces into the parent
3474 // scope?
3475 if (DebuggerTuning == llvm::DebuggerKind::SCE)
3476 CmdArgs.push_back("-dwarf-explicit-import");
3477
3478 RenderDebugInfoCompressionArgs(Args, CmdArgs, D, TC);
3479}
3480
3481void Clang::ConstructJob(Compilation &C, const JobAction &JA,
3482 const InputInfo &Output, const InputInfoList &Inputs,
3483 const ArgList &Args, const char *LinkingOutput) const {
3484 const auto &TC = getToolChain();
3485 const llvm::Triple &RawTriple = TC.getTriple();
3486 const llvm::Triple &Triple = TC.getEffectiveTriple();
3487 const std::string &TripleStr = Triple.getTriple();
3488
3489 bool KernelOrKext =
3490 Args.hasArg(options::OPT_mkernel, options::OPT_fapple_kext);
3491 const Driver &D = TC.getDriver();
3492 ArgStringList CmdArgs;
3493
3494 // Check number of inputs for sanity. We need at least one input.
3495 assert(Inputs.size() >= 1 && "Must have at least one input.");
3496 // CUDA/HIP compilation may have multiple inputs (source file + results of
3497 // device-side compilations). OpenMP device jobs also take the host IR as a
3498 // second input. Module precompilation accepts a list of header files to
3499 // include as part of the module. All other jobs are expected to have exactly
3500 // one input.
3501 bool IsCuda = JA.isOffloading(Action::OFK_Cuda);
3502 bool IsHIP = JA.isOffloading(Action::OFK_HIP);
3503 bool IsOpenMPDevice = JA.isDeviceOffloading(Action::OFK_OpenMP);
3504 bool IsHeaderModulePrecompile = isa<HeaderModulePrecompileJobAction>(JA);
3505
3506 // A header module compilation doesn't have a main input file, so invent a
3507 // fake one as a placeholder.
3508 const char *ModuleName = [&]{
3509 auto *ModuleNameArg = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_fmodule_name_EQ);
3510 return ModuleNameArg ? ModuleNameArg->getValue() : "";
3511 }();
3512 InputInfo HeaderModuleInput(Inputs[0].getType(), ModuleName, ModuleName);
3513
3514 const InputInfo &Input =
3515 IsHeaderModulePrecompile ? HeaderModuleInput : Inputs[0];
3516
3517 InputInfoList ModuleHeaderInputs;
3518 const InputInfo *CudaDeviceInput = nullptr;
3519 const InputInfo *OpenMPDeviceInput = nullptr;
3520 for (const InputInfo &I : Inputs) {
3521 if (&I == &Input) {
3522 // This is the primary input.
3523 } else if (IsHeaderModulePrecompile &&
3524 types::getPrecompiledType(I.getType()) == types::TY_PCH) {
3525 types::ID Expected = HeaderModuleInput.getType();
3526 if (I.getType() != Expected) {
3527 D.Diag(diag::err_drv_module_header_wrong_kind)
3528 << I.getFilename() << types::getTypeName(I.getType())
3529 << types::getTypeName(Expected);
3530 }
3531 ModuleHeaderInputs.push_back(I);
3532 } else if ((IsCuda || IsHIP) && !CudaDeviceInput) {
3533 CudaDeviceInput = &I;
3534 } else if (IsOpenMPDevice && !OpenMPDeviceInput) {
3535 OpenMPDeviceInput = &I;
3536 } else {
3537 llvm_unreachable("unexpectedly given multiple inputs");
3538 }
3539 }
3540
3541 const llvm::Triple *AuxTriple = IsCuda ? TC.getAuxTriple() : nullptr;
3542 bool IsWindowsGNU = RawTriple.isWindowsGNUEnvironment();
3543 bool IsWindowsCygnus = RawTriple.isWindowsCygwinEnvironment();
3544 bool IsWindowsMSVC = RawTriple.isWindowsMSVCEnvironment();
3545 bool IsIAMCU = RawTriple.isOSIAMCU();
3546
3547 // Adjust IsWindowsXYZ for CUDA/HIP compilations. Even when compiling in
3548 // device mode (i.e., getToolchain().getTriple() is NVPTX/AMDGCN, not
3549 // Windows), we need to pass Windows-specific flags to cc1.
3550 if (IsCuda || IsHIP) {
3551 IsWindowsMSVC |= AuxTriple && AuxTriple->isWindowsMSVCEnvironment();
3552 IsWindowsGNU |= AuxTriple && AuxTriple->isWindowsGNUEnvironment();
3553 IsWindowsCygnus |= AuxTriple && AuxTriple->isWindowsCygwinEnvironment();
3554 }
3555
3556 // C++ is not supported for IAMCU.
3557 if (IsIAMCU && types::isCXX(Input.getType()))
3558 D.Diag(diag::err_drv_clang_unsupported) << "C++ for IAMCU";
3559
3560 // Invoke ourselves in -cc1 mode.
3561 //
3562 // FIXME: Implement custom jobs for internal actions.
3563 CmdArgs.push_back("-cc1");
3564
3565 // Add the "effective" target triple.
3566 CmdArgs.push_back("-triple");
3567 CmdArgs.push_back(Args.MakeArgString(TripleStr));
3568
3569 if (const Arg *MJ = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_MJ)) {
3570 DumpCompilationDatabase(C, MJ->getValue(), TripleStr, Output, Input, Args);
3571 Args.ClaimAllArgs(options::OPT_MJ);
3572 }
3573
3574 if (IsCuda || IsHIP) {
3575 // We have to pass the triple of the host if compiling for a CUDA/HIP device
3576 // and vice-versa.
3577 std::string NormalizedTriple;
3578 if (JA.isDeviceOffloading(Action::OFK_Cuda) ||
3579 JA.isDeviceOffloading(Action::OFK_HIP))
3580 NormalizedTriple = C.getSingleOffloadToolChain<Action::OFK_Host>()
3581 ->getTriple()
3582 .normalize();
3583 else {
3584 // Host-side compilation.
3585 NormalizedTriple =
3586 (IsCuda ? C.getSingleOffloadToolChain<Action::OFK_Cuda>()
3587 : C.getSingleOffloadToolChain<Action::OFK_HIP>())
3588 ->getTriple()
3589 .normalize();
3590 if (IsCuda) {
3591 // We need to figure out which CUDA version we're compiling for, as that
3592 // determines how we load and launch GPU kernels.
3593 auto *CTC = static_cast<const toolchains::CudaToolChain *>(
3594 C.getSingleOffloadToolChain<Action::OFK_Cuda>());
3595 assert(CTC && "Expected valid CUDA Toolchain.");
3596 if (CTC && CTC->CudaInstallation.version() != CudaVersion::UNKNOWN)
3597 CmdArgs.push_back(Args.MakeArgString(
3598 Twine("-target-sdk-version=") +
3599 CudaVersionToString(CTC->CudaInstallation.version())));
3600 }
3601 }
3602 CmdArgs.push_back("-aux-triple");
3603 CmdArgs.push_back(Args.MakeArgString(NormalizedTriple));
3604 }
3605
3606 if (IsOpenMPDevice) {
3607 // We have to pass the triple of the host if compiling for an OpenMP device.
3608 std::string NormalizedTriple =
3609 C.getSingleOffloadToolChain<Action::OFK_Host>()
3610 ->getTriple()
3611 .normalize();
3612 CmdArgs.push_back("-aux-triple");
3613 CmdArgs.push_back(Args.MakeArgString(NormalizedTriple));
3614 }
3615
3616 if (Triple.isOSWindows() && (Triple.getArch() == llvm::Triple::arm ||
3617 Triple.getArch() == llvm::Triple::thumb)) {
3618 unsigned Offset = Triple.getArch() == llvm::Triple::arm ? 4 : 6;
3619 unsigned Version;
3620 Triple.getArchName().substr(Offset).getAsInteger(10, Version);
3621 if (Version < 7)
3622 D.Diag(diag::err_target_unsupported_arch) << Triple.getArchName()
3623 << TripleStr;
3624 }
3625
3626 // Push all default warning arguments that are specific to
3627 // the given target. These come before user provided warning options
3628 // are provided.
3629 TC.addClangWarningOptions(CmdArgs);
3630
3631 // Select the appropriate action.
3632 RewriteKind rewriteKind = RK_None;
3633
3634 if (isa<AnalyzeJobAction>(JA)) {
3635 assert(JA.getType() == types::TY_Plist && "Invalid output type.");
3636 CmdArgs.push_back("-analyze");
3637 } else if (isa<MigrateJobAction>(JA)) {
3638 CmdArgs.push_back("-migrate");
3639 } else if (isa<PreprocessJobAction>(JA)) {
3640 if (Output.getType() == types::TY_Dependencies)
3641 CmdArgs.push_back("-Eonly");
3642 else {
3643 CmdArgs.push_back("-E");
3644 if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT_rewrite_objc) &&
3645 !Args.hasArg(options::OPT_g_Group))
3646 CmdArgs.push_back("-P");
3647 }
3648 } else if (isa<AssembleJobAction>(JA)) {
3649 CmdArgs.push_back("-emit-obj");
3650
3651 CollectArgsForIntegratedAssembler(C, Args, CmdArgs, D);
3652
3653 // Also ignore explicit -force_cpusubtype_ALL option.
3654 (void)Args.hasArg(options::OPT_force__cpusubtype__ALL);
3655 } else if (isa<PrecompileJobAction>(JA)) {
3656 if (JA.getType() == types::TY_Nothing)
3657 CmdArgs.push_back("-fsyntax-only");
3658 else if (JA.getType() == types::TY_ModuleFile)
3659 CmdArgs.push_back(IsHeaderModulePrecompile
3660 ? "-emit-header-module"
3661 : "-emit-module-interface");
3662 else
3663 CmdArgs.push_back("-emit-pch");
3664 } else if (isa<VerifyPCHJobAction>(JA)) {
3665 CmdArgs.push_back("-verify-pch");
3666 } else {
3667 assert((isa<CompileJobAction>(JA) || isa<BackendJobAction>(JA)) &&
3668 "Invalid action for clang tool.");
3669 if (JA.getType() == types::TY_Nothing) {
3670 CmdArgs.push_back("-fsyntax-only");
3671 } else if (JA.getType() == types::TY_LLVM_IR ||
3672 JA.getType() == types::TY_LTO_IR) {
3673 CmdArgs.push_back("-emit-llvm");
3674 } else if (JA.getType() == types::TY_LLVM_BC ||
3675 JA.getType() == types::TY_LTO_BC) {
3676 CmdArgs.push_back("-emit-llvm-bc");
3677 } else if (JA.getType() == types::TY_PP_Asm) {
3678 CmdArgs.push_back("-S");
3679 } else if (JA.getType() == types::TY_AST) {
3680 CmdArgs.push_back("-emit-pch");
3681 } else if (JA.getType() == types::TY_ModuleFile) {
3682 CmdArgs.push_back("-module-file-info");
3683 } else if (JA.getType() == types::TY_RewrittenObjC) {
3684 CmdArgs.push_back("-rewrite-objc");
3685 rewriteKind = RK_NonFragile;
3686 } else if (JA.getType() == types::TY_RewrittenLegacyObjC) {
3687 CmdArgs.push_back("-rewrite-objc");
3688 rewriteKind = RK_Fragile;
3689 } else {
3690 assert(JA.getType() == types::TY_PP_Asm && "Unexpected output type!");
3691 }
3692
3693 // Preserve use-list order by default when emitting bitcode, so that
3694 // loading the bitcode up in 'opt' or 'llc' and running passes gives the
3695 // same result as running passes here. For LTO, we don't need to preserve
3696 // the use-list order, since serialization to bitcode is part of the flow.
3697 if (JA.getType() == types::TY_LLVM_BC)
3698 CmdArgs.push_back("-emit-llvm-uselists");
3699
3700 // Device-side jobs do not support LTO.
3701 bool isDeviceOffloadAction = !(JA.isDeviceOffloading(Action::OFK_None) ||
3702 JA.isDeviceOffloading(Action::OFK_Host));
3703
3704 if (D.isUsingLTO() && !isDeviceOffloadAction) {
3705 Args.AddLastArg(CmdArgs, options::OPT_flto, options::OPT_flto_EQ);
3706
3707 // The Darwin and PS4 linkers currently use the legacy LTO API, which
3708 // does not support LTO unit features (CFI, whole program vtable opt)
3709 // under ThinLTO.
3710 if (!(RawTriple.isOSDarwin() || RawTriple.isPS4()) ||
3711 D.getLTOMode() == LTOK_Full)
3712 CmdArgs.push_back("-flto-unit");
3713 }
3714 }
3715
3716 if (const Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_fthinlto_index_EQ)) {
3717 if (!types::isLLVMIR(Input.getType()))
3718 D.Diag(diag::err_drv_argument_only_allowed_with) << A->getAsString(Args)
3719 << "-x ir";
3720 Args.AddLastArg(CmdArgs, options::OPT_fthinlto_index_EQ);
3721 }
3722
3723 if (Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_save_temps_EQ))
3724 Args.AddLastArg(CmdArgs, options::OPT_save_temps_EQ);
3725
3726 // Embed-bitcode option.
3727 // Only white-listed flags below are allowed to be embedded.
3728 if (C.getDriver().embedBitcodeInObject() && !C.getDriver().isUsingLTO() &&
3729 (isa<BackendJobAction>(JA) || isa<AssembleJobAction>(JA))) {
3730 // Add flags implied by -fembed-bitcode.
3731 Args.AddLastArg(CmdArgs, options::OPT_fembed_bitcode_EQ);
3732 // Disable all llvm IR level optimizations.
3733 CmdArgs.push_back("-disable-llvm-passes");
3734
3735 // Render target options such as -fuse-init-array on modern ELF platforms.
3736 TC.addClangTargetOptions(Args, CmdArgs, JA.getOffloadingDeviceKind());
3737
3738 // reject options that shouldn't be supported in bitcode
3739 // also reject kernel/kext
3740 static const constexpr unsigned kBitcodeOptionBlacklist[] = {
3741 options::OPT_mkernel,
3742 options::OPT_fapple_kext,
3743 options::OPT_ffunction_sections,
3744 options::OPT_fno_function_sections,
3745 options::OPT_fdata_sections,
3746 options::OPT_fno_data_sections,
3747 options::OPT_funique_section_names,
3748 options::OPT_fno_unique_section_names,
3749 options::OPT_mrestrict_it,
3750 options::OPT_mno_restrict_it,
3751 options::OPT_mstackrealign,
3752 options::OPT_mno_stackrealign,
3753 options::OPT_mstack_alignment,
3754 options::OPT_mcmodel_EQ,
3755 options::OPT_mlong_calls,
3756 options::OPT_mno_long_calls,
3757 options::OPT_ggnu_pubnames,
3758 options::OPT_gdwarf_aranges,
3759 options::OPT_fdebug_types_section,
3760 options::OPT_fno_debug_types_section,
3761 options::OPT_fdwarf_directory_asm,
3762 options::OPT_fno_dwarf_directory_asm,
3763 options::OPT_mrelax_all,
3764 options::OPT_mno_relax_all,
3765 options::OPT_ftrap_function_EQ,
3766 options::OPT_ffixed_r9,
3767 options::OPT_mfix_cortex_a53_835769,
3768 options::OPT_mno_fix_cortex_a53_835769,
3769 options::OPT_ffixed_x18,
3770 options::OPT_mglobal_merge,
3771 options::OPT_mno_global_merge,
3772 options::OPT_mred_zone,
3773 options::OPT_mno_red_zone,
3774 options::OPT_Wa_COMMA,
3775 options::OPT_Xassembler,
3776 options::OPT_mllvm,
3777 };
3778 for (const auto &A : Args)
3779 if (llvm::find(kBitcodeOptionBlacklist, A->getOption().getID()) !=
3780 std::end(kBitcodeOptionBlacklist))
3781 D.Diag(diag::err_drv_unsupported_embed_bitcode) << A->getSpelling();
3782
3783 // Render the CodeGen options that need to be passed.
3784 if (!Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_foptimize_sibling_calls,
3785 options::OPT_fno_optimize_sibling_calls))
3786 CmdArgs.push_back("-mdisable-tail-calls");
3787
3788 RenderFloatingPointOptions(TC, D, isOptimizationLevelFast(Args), Args,
3789 CmdArgs);
3790
3791 // Render ABI arguments
3792 switch (TC.getArch()) {
3793 default: break;
3794 case llvm::Triple::arm:
3795 case llvm::Triple::armeb:
3796 case llvm::Triple::thumbeb:
3797 RenderARMABI(Triple, Args, CmdArgs);
3798 break;
3799 case llvm::Triple::aarch64:
3800 case llvm::Triple::aarch64_be:
3801 RenderAArch64ABI(Triple, Args, CmdArgs);
3802 break;
3803 }
3804
3805 // Optimization level for CodeGen.
3806 if (const Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_O_Group)) {
3807 if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_O4)) {
3808 CmdArgs.push_back("-O3");
3809 D.Diag(diag::warn_O4_is_O3);
3810 } else {
3811 A->render(Args, CmdArgs);
3812 }
3813 }
3814
3815 // Input/Output file.
3816 if (Output.getType() == types::TY_Dependencies) {
3817 // Handled with other dependency code.
3818 } else if (Output.isFilename()) {
3819 CmdArgs.push_back("-o");
3820 CmdArgs.push_back(Output.getFilename());
3821 } else {
3822 assert(Output.isNothing() && "Input output.");
3823 }
3824
3825 for (const auto &II : Inputs) {
3826 addDashXForInput(Args, II, CmdArgs);
3827 if (II.isFilename())
3828 CmdArgs.push_back(II.getFilename());
3829 else
3830 II.getInputArg().renderAsInput(Args, CmdArgs);
3831 }
3832
3833 C.addCommand(llvm::make_unique<Command>(JA, *this, D.getClangProgramPath(),
3834 CmdArgs, Inputs));
3835 return;
3836 }
3837
3838 if (C.getDriver().embedBitcodeMarkerOnly() && !C.getDriver().isUsingLTO())
3839 CmdArgs.push_back("-fembed-bitcode=marker");
3840
3841 // We normally speed up the clang process a bit by skipping destructors at
3842 // exit, but when we're generating diagnostics we can rely on some of the
3843 // cleanup.
3844 if (!C.isForDiagnostics())
3845 CmdArgs.push_back("-disable-free");
3846
3847#ifdef NDEBUG
3848 const bool IsAssertBuild = false;
3849#else
3850 const bool IsAssertBuild = true;
3851#endif
3852
3853 // Disable the verification pass in -asserts builds.
3854 if (!IsAssertBuild)
3855 CmdArgs.push_back("-disable-llvm-verifier");
3856
3857 // Discard value names in assert builds unless otherwise specified.
3858 if (Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_fdiscard_value_names,
3859 options::OPT_fno_discard_value_names, !IsAssertBuild))
3860 CmdArgs.push_back("-discard-value-names");
3861
3862 // Set the main file name, so that debug info works even with
3863 // -save-temps.
3864 CmdArgs.push_back("-main-file-name");
3865 CmdArgs.push_back(getBaseInputName(Args, Input));
3866
3867 // Some flags which affect the language (via preprocessor
3868 // defines).
3869 if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT_static))
3870 CmdArgs.push_back("-static-define");
3871
3872 if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT_municode))
3873 CmdArgs.push_back("-DUNICODE");
3874
3875 if (isa<AnalyzeJobAction>(JA))
3876 RenderAnalyzerOptions(Args, CmdArgs, Triple, Input);
3877
3878 // Enable compatilibily mode to avoid analyzer-config related errors.
3879 // Since we can't access frontend flags through hasArg, let's manually iterate
3880 // through them.
3881 bool FoundAnalyzerConfig = false;
3882 for (auto Arg : Args.filtered(options::OPT_Xclang))
3883 if (StringRef(Arg->getValue()) == "-analyzer-config") {
3884 FoundAnalyzerConfig = true;
3885 break;
3886 }
3887 if (!FoundAnalyzerConfig)
3888 for (auto Arg : Args.filtered(options::OPT_Xanalyzer))
3889 if (StringRef(Arg->getValue()) == "-analyzer-config") {
3890 FoundAnalyzerConfig = true;
3891 break;
3892 }
3893 if (FoundAnalyzerConfig)
3894 CmdArgs.push_back("-analyzer-config-compatibility-mode=true");
3895
3896 CheckCodeGenerationOptions(D, Args);
3897
3898 unsigned FunctionAlignment = ParseFunctionAlignment(TC, Args);
3899 assert(FunctionAlignment <= 31 && "function alignment will be truncated!");
3900 if (FunctionAlignment) {
3901 CmdArgs.push_back("-function-alignment");
3902 CmdArgs.push_back(Args.MakeArgString(std::to_string(FunctionAlignment)));
3903 }
3904
3905 llvm::Reloc::Model RelocationModel;
3906 unsigned PICLevel;
3907 bool IsPIE;
3908 std::tie(RelocationModel, PICLevel, IsPIE) = ParsePICArgs(TC, Args);
3909
3910 const char *RMName = RelocationModelName(RelocationModel);
3911
3912 if ((RelocationModel == llvm::Reloc::ROPI ||
3913 RelocationModel == llvm::Reloc::ROPI_RWPI) &&
3914 types::isCXX(Input.getType()) &&
3915 !Args.hasArg(options::OPT_fallow_unsupported))
3916 D.Diag(diag::err_drv_ropi_incompatible_with_cxx);
3917
3918 if (RMName) {
3919 CmdArgs.push_back("-mrelocation-model");
3920 CmdArgs.push_back(RMName);
3921 }
3922 if (PICLevel > 0) {
3923 CmdArgs.push_back("-pic-level");
3924 CmdArgs.push_back(PICLevel == 1 ? "1" : "2");
3925 if (IsPIE)
3926 CmdArgs.push_back("-pic-is-pie");
3927 }
3928
3929 if (RelocationModel == llvm::Reloc::ROPI ||
3930 RelocationModel == llvm::Reloc::ROPI_RWPI)
3931 CmdArgs.push_back("-fropi");
3932 if (RelocationModel == llvm::Reloc::RWPI ||
3933 RelocationModel == llvm::Reloc::ROPI_RWPI)
3934 CmdArgs.push_back("-frwpi");
3935
3936 if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_meabi)) {
3937 CmdArgs.push_back("-meabi");
3938 CmdArgs.push_back(A->getValue());
3939 }
3940
3941 CmdArgs.push_back("-mthread-model");
3942 if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_mthread_model)) {
3943 if (!TC.isThreadModelSupported(A->getValue()))
3944 D.Diag(diag::err_drv_invalid_thread_model_for_target)
3945 << A->getValue() << A->getAsString(Args);
3946 CmdArgs.push_back(A->getValue());
3947 }
3948 else
3949 CmdArgs.push_back(Args.MakeArgString(TC.getThreadModel()));
3950
3951 Args.AddLastArg(CmdArgs, options::OPT_fveclib);
3952
3953 if (Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_fmerge_all_constants,
3954 options::OPT_fno_merge_all_constants, false))
3955 CmdArgs.push_back("-fmerge-all-constants");
3956
3957 if (Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_fno_delete_null_pointer_checks,
3958 options::OPT_fdelete_null_pointer_checks, false))
3959 CmdArgs.push_back("-fno-delete-null-pointer-checks");
3960
3961 // LLVM Code Generator Options.
3962
3963 if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT_frewrite_map_file) ||
3964 Args.hasArg(options::OPT_frewrite_map_file_EQ)) {
3965 for (const Arg *A : Args.filtered(options::OPT_frewrite_map_file,
3966 options::OPT_frewrite_map_file_EQ)) {
3967 StringRef Map = A->getValue();
3968 if (!llvm::sys::fs::exists(Map)) {
3969 D.Diag(diag::err_drv_no_such_file) << Map;
3970 } else {
3971 CmdArgs.push_back("-frewrite-map-file");
3972 CmdArgs.push_back(A->getValue());
3973 A->claim();
3974 }
3975 }
3976 }
3977
3978 if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_Wframe_larger_than_EQ)) {
3979 StringRef v = A->getValue();
3980 CmdArgs.push_back("-mllvm");
3981 CmdArgs.push_back(Args.MakeArgString("-warn-stack-size=" + v));
3982 A->claim();
3983 }
3984
3985 if (!Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_fjump_tables, options::OPT_fno_jump_tables,
3986 true))
3987 CmdArgs.push_back("-fno-jump-tables");
3988
3989 if (Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_fprofile_sample_accurate,
3990 options::OPT_fno_profile_sample_accurate, false))
3991 CmdArgs.push_back("-fprofile-sample-accurate");
3992
3993 if (!Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_fpreserve_as_comments,
3994 options::OPT_fno_preserve_as_comments, true))

5519 addDashXForInput(Args, Input, CmdArgs);
5520
5521 ArrayRef<InputInfo> FrontendInputs = Input;
5522 if (IsHeaderModulePrecompile)
5523 FrontendInputs = ModuleHeaderInputs;
5524 else if (Input.isNothing())
5525 FrontendInputs = {};
5526
5527 for (const InputInfo &Input : FrontendInputs) {
5528 if (Input.isFilename())
5529 CmdArgs.push_back(Input.getFilename());
5530 else
5531 Input.getInputArg().renderAsInput(Args, CmdArgs);
5532 }
5533
5534 // Finally add the compile command to the compilation.
5535 if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT__SLASH_fallback) &&
5536 Output.getType() == types::TY_Object &&
5537 (InputType == types::TY_C || InputType == types::TY_CXX)) {
5538 auto CLCommand =
5539 getCLFallback()->GetCommand(C, JA, Output, Inputs, Args, LinkingOutput);
5540 C.addCommand(llvm::make_unique<FallbackCommand>(
5541 JA, *this, Exec, CmdArgs, Inputs, std::move(CLCommand)));
5542 } else if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT__SLASH_fallback) &&
5543 isa<PrecompileJobAction>(JA)) {
5544 // In /fallback builds, run the main compilation even if the pch generation
5545 // fails, so that the main compilation's fallback to cl.exe runs.
5546 C.addCommand(llvm::make_unique<ForceSuccessCommand>(JA, *this, Exec,
5547 CmdArgs, Inputs));
5548 } else {
5549 C.addCommand(llvm::make_unique<Command>(JA, *this, Exec, CmdArgs, Inputs));
5550 }
5551
5552 // Make the compile command echo its inputs for /showFilenames.
5553 if (Output.getType() == types::TY_Object &&
5554 Args.hasFlag(options::OPT__SLASH_showFilenames,
5555 options::OPT__SLASH_showFilenames_, false)) {
5556 C.getJobs().getJobs().back()->setPrintInputFilenames(true);
5557 }
5558
5559 if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_pg))
5560 if (!shouldUseFramePointer(Args, Triple))
5561 D.Diag(diag::err_drv_argument_not_allowed_with) << "-fomit-frame-pointer"
5562 << A->getAsString(Args);
5563
5564 // Claim some arguments which clang supports automatically.
5565
5566 // -fpch-preprocess is used with gcc to add a special marker in the output to
5567 // include the PCH file.
5568 Args.ClaimAllArgs(options::OPT_fpch_preprocess);
5569
5570 // Claim some arguments which clang doesn't support, but we don't
5571 // care to warn the user about.
5572 Args.ClaimAllArgs(options::OPT_clang_ignored_f_Group);
5573 Args.ClaimAllArgs(options::OPT_clang_ignored_m_Group);
5574
5575 // Disable warnings for clang -E -emit-llvm foo.c
5576 Args.ClaimAllArgs(options::OPT_emit_llvm);
5577}

5587/// Add options related to the Objective-C runtime/ABI.
5588///
5589/// Returns true if the runtime is non-fragile.
5590ObjCRuntime Clang::AddObjCRuntimeArgs(const ArgList &args,
5591 ArgStringList &cmdArgs,
5592 RewriteKind rewriteKind) const {
5593 // Look for the controlling runtime option.
5594 Arg *runtimeArg =
5595 args.getLastArg(options::OPT_fnext_runtime, options::OPT_fgnu_runtime,
5596 options::OPT_fobjc_runtime_EQ);
5597
5598 // Just forward -fobjc-runtime= to the frontend. This supercedes
5599 // options about fragility.
5600 if (runtimeArg &&
5601 runtimeArg->getOption().matches(options::OPT_fobjc_runtime_EQ)) {
5602 ObjCRuntime runtime;
5603 StringRef value = runtimeArg->getValue();
5604 if (runtime.tryParse(value)) {
5605 getToolChain().getDriver().Diag(diag::err_drv_unknown_objc_runtime)
5606 << value;
5607 }
5608 if ((runtime.getKind() == ObjCRuntime::GNUstep) &&
5609 (runtime.getVersion() >= VersionTuple(2, 0)))
5610 if (!getToolChain().getTriple().isOSBinFormatELF() &&
5611 !getToolChain().getTriple().isOSBinFormatCOFF()) {
5612 getToolChain().getDriver().Diag(
5613 diag::err_drv_gnustep_objc_runtime_incompatible_binary)
5614 << runtime.getVersion().getMajor();
5615 }
5616
5617 runtimeArg->render(args, cmdArgs);
5618 return runtime;
5619 }
5620
5621 // Otherwise, we'll need the ABI "version". Version numbers are
5622 // slightly confusing for historical reasons:
5623 // 1 - Traditional "fragile" ABI
5624 // 2 - Non-fragile ABI, version 1
5625 // 3 - Non-fragile ABI, version 2
5626 unsigned objcABIVersion = 1;
5627 // If -fobjc-abi-version= is present, use that to set the version.
5628 if (Arg *abiArg = args.getLastArg(options::OPT_fobjc_abi_version_EQ)) {
5629 StringRef value = abiArg->getValue();
5630 if (value == "1")
5631 objcABIVersion = 1;
5632 else if (value == "2")
5633 objcABIVersion = 2;
5634 else if (value == "3")
5635 objcABIVersion = 3;
5636 else
5637 getToolChain().getDriver().Diag(diag::err_drv_clang_unsupported) << value;
5638 } else {
5639 // Otherwise, determine if we are using the non-fragile ABI.
5640 bool nonFragileABIIsDefault =
5641 (rewriteKind == RK_NonFragile ||
5642 (rewriteKind == RK_None &&
5643 getToolChain().IsObjCNonFragileABIDefault()));
5644 if (args.hasFlag(options::OPT_fobjc_nonfragile_abi,
5645 options::OPT_fno_objc_nonfragile_abi,
5646 nonFragileABIIsDefault)) {
5647// Determine the non-fragile ABI version to use.
5648#ifdef DISABLE_DEFAULT_NONFRAGILEABI_TWO
5649 unsigned nonFragileABIVersion = 1;
5650#else
5651 unsigned nonFragileABIVersion = 2;
5652#endif
5653
5654 if (Arg *abiArg =
5655 args.getLastArg(options::OPT_fobjc_nonfragile_abi_version_EQ)) {
5656 StringRef value = abiArg->getValue();
5657 if (value == "1")
5658 nonFragileABIVersion = 1;
5659 else if (value == "2")
5660 nonFragileABIVersion = 2;
5661 else
5662 getToolChain().getDriver().Diag(diag::err_drv_clang_unsupported)
5663 << value;
5664 }
5665
5666 objcABIVersion = 1 + nonFragileABIVersion;
5667 } else {
5668 objcABIVersion = 1;
5669 }
5670 }
5671
5672 // We don't actually care about the ABI version other than whether
5673 // it's non-fragile.
5674 bool isNonFragile = objcABIVersion != 1;
5675
5676 // If we have no runtime argument, ask the toolchain for its default runtime.
5677 // However, the rewriter only really supports the Mac runtime, so assume that.
5678 ObjCRuntime runtime;
5679 if (!runtimeArg) {
5680 switch (rewriteKind) {
5681 case RK_None:
5682 runtime = getToolChain().getDefaultObjCRuntime(isNonFragile);
5683 break;
5684 case RK_Fragile:
5685 runtime = ObjCRuntime(ObjCRuntime::FragileMacOSX, VersionTuple());
5686 break;
5687 case RK_NonFragile:
5688 runtime = ObjCRuntime(ObjCRuntime::MacOSX, VersionTuple());
5689 break;
5690 }
5691
5692 // -fnext-runtime
5693 } else if (runtimeArg->getOption().matches(options::OPT_fnext_runtime)) {
5694 // On Darwin, make this use the default behavior for the toolchain.
5695 if (getToolChain().getTriple().isOSDarwin()) {
5696 runtime = getToolChain().getDefaultObjCRuntime(isNonFragile);
5697
5698 // Otherwise, build for a generic macosx port.
5699 } else {
5700 runtime = ObjCRuntime(ObjCRuntime::MacOSX, VersionTuple());
5701 }
5702
5703 // -fgnu-runtime
5704 } else {
5705 assert(runtimeArg->getOption().matches(options::OPT_fgnu_runtime));
5706 // Legacy behaviour is to target the gnustep runtime if we are in
5707 // non-fragile mode or the GCC runtime in fragile mode.
5708 if (isNonFragile)
5709 runtime = ObjCRuntime(ObjCRuntime::GNUstep, VersionTuple(2, 0));
5710 else
5711 runtime = ObjCRuntime(ObjCRuntime::GCC, VersionTuple());
5712 }
5713
5714 cmdArgs.push_back(
5715 args.MakeArgString("-fobjc-runtime=" + runtime.getAsString()));
5716 return runtime;
5717}
5718
5719static bool maybeConsumeDash(const std::string &EH, size_t &I) {
5720 bool HaveDash = (I + 1 < EH.size() && EH[I + 1] == '-');
5721 I += HaveDash;
5722 return !HaveDash;
5723}
5724
5725namespace {
5726struct EHFlags {
5727 bool Synch = false;
5728 bool Asynch = false;
5729 bool NoUnwindC = false;
5730};
5731} // end anonymous namespace
5732
5733/// /EH controls whether to run destructor cleanups when exceptions are
5734/// thrown. There are three modifiers:
5735/// - s: Cleanup after "synchronous" exceptions, aka C++ exceptions.
5736/// - a: Cleanup after "asynchronous" exceptions, aka structured exceptions.
5737/// The 'a' modifier is unimplemented and fundamentally hard in LLVM IR.
5738/// - c: Assume that extern "C" functions are implicitly nounwind.
5739/// The default is /EHs-c-, meaning cleanups are disabled.
5740static EHFlags parseClangCLEHFlags(const Driver &D, const ArgList &Args) {
5741 EHFlags EH;
5742
5743 std::vector<std::string> EHArgs =
5744 Args.getAllArgValues(options::OPT__SLASH_EH);
5745 for (auto EHVal : EHArgs) {
5746 for (size_t I = 0, E = EHVal.size(); I != E; ++I) {
5747 switch (EHVal[I]) {
5748 case 'a':
5749 EH.Asynch = maybeConsumeDash(EHVal, I);
5750 if (EH.Asynch)
5751 EH.Synch = false;
5752 continue;
5753 case 'c':
5754 EH.NoUnwindC = maybeConsumeDash(EHVal, I);
5755 continue;
5756 case 's':
5757 EH.Synch = maybeConsumeDash(EHVal, I);
5758 if (EH.Synch)
5759 EH.Asynch = false;
5760 continue;
5761 default:
5762 break;
5763 }
5764 D.Diag(clang::diag::err_drv_invalid_value) << "/EH" << EHVal;
5765 break;
5766 }
5767 }
5768 // The /GX, /GX- flags are only processed if there are not /EH flags.
5769 // The default is that /GX is not specified.
5770 if (EHArgs.empty() &&
5771 Args.hasFlag(options::OPT__SLASH_GX, options::OPT__SLASH_GX_,
5772 /*default=*/false)) {
5773 EH.Synch = true;
5774 EH.NoUnwindC = true;
5775 }
5776
5777 return EH;
5778}
5779
5780void Clang::AddClangCLArgs(const ArgList &Args, types::ID InputType,
5781 ArgStringList &CmdArgs,
5782 codegenoptions::DebugInfoKind *DebugInfoKind,
5783 bool *EmitCodeView) const {
5784 unsigned RTOptionID = options::OPT__SLASH_MT;
5785
5786 if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT__SLASH_LDd))
5787 // The /LDd option implies /MTd. The dependent lib part can be overridden,
5788 // but defining _DEBUG is sticky.
5789 RTOptionID = options::OPT__SLASH_MTd;
5790
5791 if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT__SLASH_M_Group))
5792 RTOptionID = A->getOption().getID();
5793
5794 StringRef FlagForCRT;
5795 switch (RTOptionID) {
5796 case options::OPT__SLASH_MD:
5797 if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT__SLASH_LDd))
5798 CmdArgs.push_back("-D_DEBUG");
5799 CmdArgs.push_back("-D_MT");
5800 CmdArgs.push_back("-D_DLL");
5801 FlagForCRT = "--dependent-lib=msvcrt";
5802 break;
5803 case options::OPT__SLASH_MDd:
5804 CmdArgs.push_back("-D_DEBUG");
5805 CmdArgs.push_back("-D_MT");
5806 CmdArgs.push_back("-D_DLL");
5807 FlagForCRT = "--dependent-lib=msvcrtd";
5808 break;
5809 case options::OPT__SLASH_MT:
5810 if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT__SLASH_LDd))
5811 CmdArgs.push_back("-D_DEBUG");
5812 CmdArgs.push_back("-D_MT");
5813 CmdArgs.push_back("-flto-visibility-public-std");
5814 FlagForCRT = "--dependent-lib=libcmt";
5815 break;
5816 case options::OPT__SLASH_MTd:
5817 CmdArgs.push_back("-D_DEBUG");
5818 CmdArgs.push_back("-D_MT");
5819 CmdArgs.push_back("-flto-visibility-public-std");
5820 FlagForCRT = "--dependent-lib=libcmtd";
5821 break;
5822 default:
5823 llvm_unreachable("Unexpected option ID.");
5824 }
5825
5826 if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT__SLASH_Zl)) {
5827 CmdArgs.push_back("-D_VC_NODEFAULTLIB");
5828 } else {
5829 CmdArgs.push_back(FlagForCRT.data());
5830
5831 // This provides POSIX compatibility (maps 'open' to '_open'), which most
5832 // users want. The /Za flag to cl.exe turns this off, but it's not
5833 // implemented in clang.
5834 CmdArgs.push_back("--dependent-lib=oldnames");
5835 }
5836
5837 if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_show_includes))
5838 A->render(Args, CmdArgs);
5839
5840 // This controls whether or not we emit RTTI data for polymorphic types.
5841 if (Args.hasFlag(options::OPT__SLASH_GR_, options::OPT__SLASH_GR,
5842 /*default=*/false))
5843 CmdArgs.push_back("-fno-rtti-data");
5844
5845 // This controls whether or not we emit stack-protector instrumentation.
5846 // In MSVC, Buffer Security Check (/GS) is on by default.
5847 if (Args.hasFlag(options::OPT__SLASH_GS, options::OPT__SLASH_GS_,
5848 /*default=*/true)) {
5849 CmdArgs.push_back("-stack-protector");
5850 CmdArgs.push_back(Args.MakeArgString(Twine(LangOptions::SSPStrong)));
5851 }
5852
5853 // Emit CodeView if -Z7, -Zd, or -gline-tables-only are present.
5854 if (Arg *DebugInfoArg =
5855 Args.getLastArg(options::OPT__SLASH_Z7, options::OPT__SLASH_Zd,
5856 options::OPT_gline_tables_only)) {
5857 *EmitCodeView = true;
5858 if (DebugInfoArg->getOption().matches(options::OPT__SLASH_Z7))
5859 *DebugInfoKind = codegenoptions::LimitedDebugInfo;
5860 else
5861 *DebugInfoKind = codegenoptions::DebugLineTablesOnly;
5862 } else {
5863 *EmitCodeView = false;
5864 }
5865
5866 const Driver &D = getToolChain().getDriver();
5867 EHFlags EH = parseClangCLEHFlags(D, Args);
5868 if (EH.Synch || EH.Asynch) {
5869 if (types::isCXX(InputType))
5870 CmdArgs.push_back("-fcxx-exceptions");
5871 CmdArgs.push_back("-fexceptions");
5872 }
5873 if (types::isCXX(InputType) && EH.Synch && EH.NoUnwindC)
5874 CmdArgs.push_back("-fexternc-nounwind");
5875
5876 // /EP should expand to -E -P.
5877 if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT__SLASH_EP)) {
5878 CmdArgs.push_back("-E");
5879 CmdArgs.push_back("-P");
5880 }
5881
5882 unsigned VolatileOptionID;
5883 if (getToolChain().getArch() == llvm::Triple::x86_64 ||
5884 getToolChain().getArch() == llvm::Triple::x86)
5885 VolatileOptionID = options::OPT__SLASH_volatile_ms;
5886 else
5887 VolatileOptionID = options::OPT__SLASH_volatile_iso;
5888
5889 if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT__SLASH_volatile_Group))
5890 VolatileOptionID = A->getOption().getID();
5891
5892 if (VolatileOptionID == options::OPT__SLASH_volatile_ms)
5893 CmdArgs.push_back("-fms-volatile");
5894
5895 if (Args.hasFlag(options::OPT__SLASH_Zc_dllexportInlines_,
5896 options::OPT__SLASH_Zc_dllexportInlines,
5897 false)) {
5898 if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT__SLASH_fallback)) {
5899 D.Diag(clang::diag::err_drv_dllexport_inlines_and_fallback);
5900 } else {
5901 CmdArgs.push_back("-fno-dllexport-inlines");
5902 }
5903 }
5904
5905 Arg *MostGeneralArg = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT__SLASH_vmg);
5906 Arg *BestCaseArg = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT__SLASH_vmb);
5907 if (MostGeneralArg && BestCaseArg)
5908 D.Diag(clang::diag::err_drv_argument_not_allowed_with)
5909 << MostGeneralArg->getAsString(Args) << BestCaseArg->getAsString(Args);
5910
5911 if (MostGeneralArg) {
5912 Arg *SingleArg = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT__SLASH_vms);
5913 Arg *MultipleArg = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT__SLASH_vmm);
5914 Arg *VirtualArg = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT__SLASH_vmv);
5915
5916 Arg *FirstConflict = SingleArg ? SingleArg : MultipleArg;
5917 Arg *SecondConflict = VirtualArg ? VirtualArg : MultipleArg;
5918 if (FirstConflict && SecondConflict && FirstConflict != SecondConflict)
5919 D.Diag(clang::diag::err_drv_argument_not_allowed_with)
5920 << FirstConflict->getAsString(Args)
5921 << SecondConflict->getAsString(Args);
5922
5923 if (SingleArg)
5924 CmdArgs.push_back("-fms-memptr-rep=single");
5925 else if (MultipleArg)
5926 CmdArgs.push_back("-fms-memptr-rep=multiple");
5927 else
5928 CmdArgs.push_back("-fms-memptr-rep=virtual");
5929 }
5930
5931 // Parse the default calling convention options.
5932 if (Arg *CCArg =
5933 Args.getLastArg(options::OPT__SLASH_Gd, options::OPT__SLASH_Gr,
5934 options::OPT__SLASH_Gz, options::OPT__SLASH_Gv,
5935 options::OPT__SLASH_Gregcall)) {
5936 unsigned DCCOptId = CCArg->getOption().getID();
5937 const char *DCCFlag = nullptr;
5938 bool ArchSupported = true;
5939 llvm::Triple::ArchType Arch = getToolChain().getArch();
5940 switch (DCCOptId) {
5941 case options::OPT__SLASH_Gd:
5942 DCCFlag = "-fdefault-calling-conv=cdecl";
5943 break;
5944 case options::OPT__SLASH_Gr:
5945 ArchSupported = Arch == llvm::Triple::x86;
5946 DCCFlag = "-fdefault-calling-conv=fastcall";
5947 break;
5948 case options::OPT__SLASH_Gz:
5949 ArchSupported = Arch == llvm::Triple::x86;
5950 DCCFlag = "-fdefault-calling-conv=stdcall";
5951 break;
5952 case options::OPT__SLASH_Gv:
5953 ArchSupported = Arch == llvm::Triple::x86 || Arch == llvm::Triple::x86_64;
5954 DCCFlag = "-fdefault-calling-conv=vectorcall";
5955 break;
5956 case options::OPT__SLASH_Gregcall:
5957 ArchSupported = Arch == llvm::Triple::x86 || Arch == llvm::Triple::x86_64;
5958 DCCFlag = "-fdefault-calling-conv=regcall";
5959 break;
5960 }
5961
5962 // MSVC doesn't warn if /Gr or /Gz is used on x64, so we don't either.
5963 if (ArchSupported && DCCFlag)
5964 CmdArgs.push_back(DCCFlag);
5965 }
5966
5967 if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_vtordisp_mode_EQ))
5968 A->render(Args, CmdArgs);
5969
5970 if (!Args.hasArg(options::OPT_fdiagnostics_format_EQ)) {
5971 CmdArgs.push_back("-fdiagnostics-format");
5972 if (Args.hasArg(options::OPT__SLASH_fallback))
5973 CmdArgs.push_back("msvc-fallback");
5974 else
5975 CmdArgs.push_back("msvc");
5976 }
5977
5978 if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT__SLASH_guard)) {
5979 SmallVector<StringRef, 1> SplitArgs;
5980 StringRef(A->getValue()).split(SplitArgs, ",");
5981 bool Instrument = false;
5982 bool NoChecks = false;
5983 for (StringRef Arg : SplitArgs) {
5984 if (Arg.equals_lower("cf"))
5985 Instrument = true;
5986 else if (Arg.equals_lower("cf-"))
5987 Instrument = false;
5988 else if (Arg.equals_lower("nochecks"))
5989 NoChecks = true;
5990 else if (Arg.equals_lower("nochecks-"))
5991 NoChecks = false;
5992 else
5993 D.Diag(diag::err_drv_invalid_value) << A->getSpelling() << Arg;
5994 }
5995 // Currently there's no support emitting CFG instrumentation; the flag only
5996 // emits the table of address-taken functions.
5997 if (Instrument || NoChecks)
5998 CmdArgs.push_back("-cfguard");
5999 }
6000}

6075
6076void ClangAs::ConstructJob(Compilation &C, const JobAction &JA,
6077 const InputInfo &Output, const InputInfoList &Inputs,
6078 const ArgList &Args,
6079 const char *LinkingOutput) const {
6080 ArgStringList CmdArgs;
6081
6082 assert(Inputs.size() == 1 && "Unexpected number of inputs.");
6083 const InputInfo &Input = Inputs[0];
6084
6085 const llvm::Triple &Triple = getToolChain().getEffectiveTriple();
6086 const std::string &TripleStr = Triple.getTriple();
6087 const auto &D = getToolChain().getDriver();
6088
6089 // Don't warn about "clang -w -c foo.s"
6090 Args.ClaimAllArgs(options::OPT_w);
6091 // and "clang -emit-llvm -c foo.s"
6092 Args.ClaimAllArgs(options::OPT_emit_llvm);
6093
6094 claimNoWarnArgs(Args);
6095
6096 // Invoke ourselves in -cc1as mode.
6097 //
6098 // FIXME: Implement custom jobs for internal actions.
6099 CmdArgs.push_back("-cc1as");
6100
6101 // Add the "effective" target triple.
6102 CmdArgs.push_back("-triple");
6103 CmdArgs.push_back(Args.MakeArgString(TripleStr));
6104
6105 // Set the output mode, we currently only expect to be used as a real
6106 // assembler.
6107 CmdArgs.push_back("-filetype");
6108 CmdArgs.push_back("obj");
6109
6110 // Set the main file name, so that debug info works even with
6111 // -save-temps or preprocessed assembly.
6112 CmdArgs.push_back("-main-file-name");
6113 CmdArgs.push_back(Clang::getBaseInputName(Args, Input));
6114
6115 // Add the target cpu
6116 std::string CPU = getCPUName(Args, Triple, /*FromAs*/ true);
6117 if (!CPU.empty()) {
6118 CmdArgs.push_back("-target-cpu");
6119 CmdArgs.push_back(Args.MakeArgString(CPU));
6120 }
6121
6122 // Add the target features
6123 getTargetFeatures(getToolChain(), Triple, Args, CmdArgs, true);
6124
6125 // Ignore explicit -force_cpusubtype_ALL option.
6126 (void)Args.hasArg(options::OPT_force__cpusubtype__ALL);
6127
6128 // Pass along any -I options so we get proper .include search paths.
6129 Args.AddAllArgs(CmdArgs, options::OPT_I_Group);
6130
6131 // Determine the original source input.
6132 const Action *SourceAction = &JA;
6133 while (SourceAction->getKind() != Action::InputClass) {
6134 assert(!SourceAction->getInputs().empty() && "unexpected root action!");
6135 SourceAction = SourceAction->getInputs()[0];
6136 }
6137
6138 // Forward -g and handle debug info related flags, assuming we are dealing
6139 // with an actual assembly file.
6140 bool WantDebug = false;
6141 unsigned DwarfVersion = 0;
6142 Args.ClaimAllArgs(options::OPT_g_Group);
6143 if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_g_Group)) {
6144 WantDebug = !A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_g0) &&
6145 !A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_ggdb0);
6146 if (WantDebug)
6147 DwarfVersion = DwarfVersionNum(A->getSpelling());
6148 }
6149 if (DwarfVersion == 0)
6150 DwarfVersion = getToolChain().GetDefaultDwarfVersion();
6151
6152 codegenoptions::DebugInfoKind DebugInfoKind = codegenoptions::NoDebugInfo;
6153
6154 if (SourceAction->getType() == types::TY_Asm ||
6155 SourceAction->getType() == types::TY_PP_Asm) {
6156 // You might think that it would be ok to set DebugInfoKind outside of
6157 // the guard for source type, however there is a test which asserts
6158 // that some assembler invocation receives no -debug-info-kind,
6159 // and it's not clear whether that test is just overly restrictive.
6160 DebugInfoKind = (WantDebug ? codegenoptions::LimitedDebugInfo
6161 : codegenoptions::NoDebugInfo);
6162 // Add the -fdebug-compilation-dir flag if needed.
6163 addDebugCompDirArg(Args, CmdArgs, C.getDriver().getVFS());
6164
6165 addDebugPrefixMapArg(getToolChain().getDriver(), Args, CmdArgs);
6166
6167 // Set the AT_producer to the clang version when using the integrated
6168 // assembler on assembly source files.
6169 CmdArgs.push_back("-dwarf-debug-producer");
6170 CmdArgs.push_back(Args.MakeArgString(getClangFullVersion()));
6171
6172 // And pass along -I options
6173 Args.AddAllArgs(CmdArgs, options::OPT_I);
6174 }
6175 RenderDebugEnablingArgs(Args, CmdArgs, DebugInfoKind, DwarfVersion,
6176 llvm::DebuggerKind::Default);
6177 RenderDebugInfoCompressionArgs(Args, CmdArgs, D, getToolChain());
6178
6179
6180 // Handle -fPIC et al -- the relocation-model affects the assembler
6181 // for some targets.
6182 llvm::Reloc::Model RelocationModel;
6183 unsigned PICLevel;
6184 bool IsPIE;
6185 std::tie(RelocationModel, PICLevel, IsPIE) =
6186 ParsePICArgs(getToolChain(), Args);
6187
6188 const char *RMName = RelocationModelName(RelocationModel);
6189 if (RMName) {
6190 CmdArgs.push_back("-mrelocation-model");
6191 CmdArgs.push_back(RMName);
6192 }
6193
6194 // Optionally embed the -cc1as level arguments into the debug info, for build
6195 // analysis.
6196 if (getToolChain().UseDwarfDebugFlags()) {
6197 ArgStringList OriginalArgs;
6198 for (const auto &Arg : Args)
6199 Arg->render(Args, OriginalArgs);
6200
6201 SmallString<256> Flags;
6202 const char *Exec = getToolChain().getDriver().getClangProgramPath();
6203 Flags += Exec;
6204 for (const char *OriginalArg : OriginalArgs) {
6205 SmallString<128> EscapedArg;
6206 EscapeSpacesAndBackslashes(OriginalArg, EscapedArg);
6207 Flags += " ";
6208 Flags += EscapedArg;
6209 }
6210 CmdArgs.push_back("-dwarf-debug-flags");
6211 CmdArgs.push_back(Args.MakeArgString(Flags));
6212 }
6213
6214 // FIXME: Add -static support, once we have it.
6215
6216 // Add target specific flags.
6217 switch (getToolChain().getArch()) {
6218 default:
6219 break;
6220
6221 case llvm::Triple::mips:
6222 case llvm::Triple::mipsel:
6223 case llvm::Triple::mips64:
6224 case llvm::Triple::mips64el:
6225 case llvm::Triple::cheri:
6226 AddMIPSTargetArgs(Args, CmdArgs);
6227 break;
6228
6229 case llvm::Triple::x86:
6230 case llvm::Triple::x86_64:
6231 AddX86TargetArgs(Args, CmdArgs);
6232 break;
6233
6234 case llvm::Triple::arm:
6235 case llvm::Triple::armeb:
6236 case llvm::Triple::thumb:
6237 case llvm::Triple::thumbeb:
6238 // This isn't in AddARMTargetArgs because we want to do this for assembly
6239 // only, not C/C++.
6240 if (Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_mdefault_build_attributes,
6241 options::OPT_mno_default_build_attributes, true)) {
6242 CmdArgs.push_back("-mllvm");
6243 CmdArgs.push_back("-arm-add-build-attributes");
6244 }
6245 break;
6246
6247 case llvm::Triple::riscv32:
6248 case llvm::Triple::riscv64:
6249 AddRISCVTargetArgs(Args, CmdArgs);
6250 break;
6251 }
6252
6253 // Consume all the warning flags. Usually this would be handled more
6254 // gracefully by -cc1 (warning about unknown warning flags, etc) but -cc1as
6255 // doesn't handle that so rather than warning about unused flags that are
6256 // actually used, we'll lie by omission instead.
6257 // FIXME: Stop lying and consume only the appropriate driver flags
6258 Args.ClaimAllArgs(options::OPT_W_Group);
6259
6260 CollectArgsForIntegratedAssembler(C, Args, CmdArgs,
6261 getToolChain().getDriver());
6262
6263 Args.AddAllArgs(CmdArgs, options::OPT_mllvm);
6264
6265 assert(Output.isFilename() && "Unexpected lipo output.");
6266 CmdArgs.push_back("-o");
6267 CmdArgs.push_back(Output.getFilename());
6268
6269 const llvm::Triple &T = getToolChain().getTriple();
6270 Arg *A;
6271 if (getDebugFissionKind(D, Args, A) == DwarfFissionKind::Split &&
6272 T.isOSBinFormatELF()) {
6273 CmdArgs.push_back("-split-dwarf-file");
6274 CmdArgs.push_back(SplitDebugName(Args, Input, Output));
6275 }
6276
6277 assert(Input.isFilename() && "Invalid input.");
6278 CmdArgs.push_back(Input.getFilename());
6279
6280 const char *Exec = getToolChain().getDriver().getClangProgramPath();
6281 C.addCommand(llvm::make_unique<Command>(JA, *this, Exec, CmdArgs, Inputs));
6282}
