6284// Begin OffloadBundler
6285
6286void OffloadBundler::ConstructJob(Compilation &C, const JobAction &JA,
6287 const InputInfo &Output,
6288 const InputInfoList &Inputs,
6289 const llvm::opt::ArgList &TCArgs,
6290 const char *LinkingOutput) const {
6291 // The version with only one output is expected to refer to a bundling job.
6292 assert(isa<OffloadBundlingJobAction>(JA) && "Expecting bundling job!");
6293
6294 // The bundling command looks like this:
6295 // clang-offload-bundler -type=bc
6296 // -targets=host-triple,openmp-triple1,openmp-triple2
6297 // -outputs=input_file
6298 // -inputs=unbundle_file_host,unbundle_file_tgt1,unbundle_file_tgt2"
6299
6300 ArgStringList CmdArgs;
6301
6302 // Get the type.
6303 CmdArgs.push_back(TCArgs.MakeArgString(
6304 Twine("-type=") + types::getTypeTempSuffix(Output.getType())));
6305
6306 assert(JA.getInputs().size() == Inputs.size() &&
6307 "Not have inputs for all dependence actions??");
6308
6309 // Get the targets.
6310 SmallString<128> Triples;
6311 Triples += "-targets=";
6312 for (unsigned I = 0; I < Inputs.size(); ++I) {
6313 if (I)
6314 Triples += ',';
6315
6316 // Find ToolChain for this input.
6317 Action::OffloadKind CurKind = Action::OFK_Host;
6318 const ToolChain *CurTC = &getToolChain();
6319 const Action *CurDep = JA.getInputs()[I];
6320
6321 if (const auto *OA = dyn_cast<OffloadAction>(CurDep)) {
6322 CurTC = nullptr;
6323 OA->doOnEachDependence([&](Action *A, const ToolChain *TC, const char *) {
6324 assert(CurTC == nullptr && "Expected one dependence!");
6325 CurKind = A->getOffloadingDeviceKind();
6326 CurTC = TC;
6327 });
6328 }
6329 Triples += Action::GetOffloadKindName(CurKind);
6330 Triples += '-';
6331 Triples += CurTC->getTriple().normalize();
6332 if (CurKind == Action::OFK_HIP && CurDep->getOffloadingArch()) {
6333 Triples += '-';
6334 Triples += CurDep->getOffloadingArch();
6335 }
6336 }
6337 CmdArgs.push_back(TCArgs.MakeArgString(Triples));
6338
6339 // Get bundled file command.
6340 CmdArgs.push_back(
6341 TCArgs.MakeArgString(Twine("-outputs=") + Output.getFilename()));
6342
6343 // Get unbundled files command.
6344 SmallString<128> UB;
6345 UB += "-inputs=";
6346 for (unsigned I = 0; I < Inputs.size(); ++I) {
6347 if (I)
6348 UB += ',';
6349
6350 // Find ToolChain for this input.
6351 const ToolChain *CurTC = &getToolChain();
6352 if (const auto *OA = dyn_cast<OffloadAction>(JA.getInputs()[I])) {
6353 CurTC = nullptr;
6354 OA->doOnEachDependence([&](Action *, const ToolChain *TC, const char *) {
6355 assert(CurTC == nullptr && "Expected one dependence!");
6356 CurTC = TC;
6357 });
6358 }
6359 UB += CurTC->getInputFilename(Inputs[I]);
6360 }
6361 CmdArgs.push_back(TCArgs.MakeArgString(UB));
6362
6363 // All the inputs are encoded as commands.
6364 C.addCommand(llvm::make_unique<Command>(
6365 JA, *this,
6366 TCArgs.MakeArgString(getToolChain().GetProgramPath(getShortName())),
6367 CmdArgs, None));
6368}
6369
6370void OffloadBundler::ConstructJobMultipleOutputs(
6371 Compilation &C, const JobAction &JA, const InputInfoList &Outputs,
6372 const InputInfoList &Inputs, const llvm::opt::ArgList &TCArgs,
6373 const char *LinkingOutput) const {
6374 // The version with multiple outputs is expected to refer to a unbundling job.
6375 auto &UA = cast<OffloadUnbundlingJobAction>(JA);
6376
6377 // The unbundling command looks like this:
6378 // clang-offload-bundler -type=bc
6379 // -targets=host-triple,openmp-triple1,openmp-triple2
6380 // -inputs=input_file
6381 // -outputs=unbundle_file_host,unbundle_file_tgt1,unbundle_file_tgt2"
6382 // -unbundle
6383
6384 ArgStringList CmdArgs;
6385
6386 assert(Inputs.size() == 1 && "Expecting to unbundle a single file!");
6387 InputInfo Input = Inputs.front();
6388
6389 // Get the type.
6390 CmdArgs.push_back(TCArgs.MakeArgString(
6391 Twine("-type=") + types::getTypeTempSuffix(Input.getType())));
6392
6393 // Get the targets.
6394 SmallString<128> Triples;
6395 Triples += "-targets=";
6396 auto DepInfo = UA.getDependentActionsInfo();
6397 for (unsigned I = 0; I < DepInfo.size(); ++I) {
6398 if (I)
6399 Triples += ',';
6400
6401 auto &Dep = DepInfo[I];
6402 Triples += Action::GetOffloadKindName(Dep.DependentOffloadKind);
6403 Triples += '-';
6404 Triples += Dep.DependentToolChain->getTriple().normalize();
6405 if (Dep.DependentOffloadKind == Action::OFK_HIP &&
6406 !Dep.DependentBoundArch.empty()) {
6407 Triples += '-';
6408 Triples += Dep.DependentBoundArch;
6409 }
6410 }
6411
6412 CmdArgs.push_back(TCArgs.MakeArgString(Triples));
6413
6414 // Get bundled file command.
6415 CmdArgs.push_back(
6416 TCArgs.MakeArgString(Twine("-inputs=") + Input.getFilename()));
6417
6418 // Get unbundled files command.
6419 SmallString<128> UB;
6420 UB += "-outputs=";
6421 for (unsigned I = 0; I < Outputs.size(); ++I) {
6422 if (I)
6423 UB += ',';
6424 UB += DepInfo[I].DependentToolChain->getInputFilename(Outputs[I]);
6425 }
6426 CmdArgs.push_back(TCArgs.MakeArgString(UB));
6427 CmdArgs.push_back("-unbundle");
6428
6429 // All the inputs are encoded as commands.
6430 C.addCommand(llvm::make_unique<Command>(
6431 JA, *this,
6432 TCArgs.MakeArgString(getToolChain().GetProgramPath(getShortName())),
6433 CmdArgs, None));
6434}
